03:19.340 --> 03:21.741
(♪♪♪)

03:41.220 --> 03:43.621
(♪♪♪)

04:03.700 --> 04:06.067
(♪♪♪)

04:19.260 --> 04:21.183
(REINS SNAPPING)

04:26.100 --> 04:28.148
(REINS SNAPPING)

04:33.700 --> 04:36.101
(♪♪♪)

04:41.140 --> 04:43.302
MAN (IN DISTANCE): Hyah! Huh!

04:43.420 --> 04:44.865
Get in there now!

04:44.980 --> 04:46.823
Get in! Get in!

04:46.940 --> 04:48.942
Get in there, Dude!

04:49.060 --> 04:50.107
- Get in now!
- (GALLOPING HOOFBEATS)

04:50.220 --> 04:54.191
Hyah! Come on! Huh!

04:54.300 --> 04:57.065
All right! Huh!

04:57.180 --> 05:00.104
- Huh!
- (HORSES SPUTTERING)

05:00.220 --> 05:03.190
Whoa. Whoa.

05:03.300 --> 05:04.950
Whoa.

05:05.060 --> 05:07.427
(HORSES SNORTING, SPUTTERING)

05:11.220 --> 05:13.507
Got room for one more?

05:13.620 --> 05:15.987
Who the hell are you?

05:16.140 --> 05:17.824
And what happened to them?

05:17.940 --> 05:19.066
(HORSE WHINNIES)

05:20.220 --> 05:23.310
Name's Major Marquis Warren,
former U.S. Cavalry.

05:23.420 --> 05:24.910
Currently a servant of the court.

05:25.020 --> 05:27.705
Trying to bring a couple
no-goods into market.

05:27.860 --> 05:29.862
Got the paperwork on 'em in my pocket.

05:29.980 --> 05:32.108
You takin' 'em into Red Rock?

05:32.220 --> 05:34.063
Figure that's where you headed, right?

05:34.180 --> 05:35.420
I am.

05:35.580 --> 05:39.068
That damn blasted blizzard has been
on our ass for the last three hours.

05:39.180 --> 05:40.944
(DISTANT THUNDER RUMBLES)

05:41.060 --> 05:43.461
There ain't no way we gonna
make it all the way to Red Rock

05:43.580 --> 05:45.947
- 'fore it catches us.
- So you hightailin' it halfway,

05:46.060 --> 05:47.186
to Minnie's Haberdashery?

05:47.340 --> 05:49.342
You know I am.

05:49.460 --> 05:50.700
May I come aboard?

05:50.820 --> 05:52.822
Well, smoke,

05:52.940 --> 05:55.989
if it up to me, yes.

05:56.140 --> 05:58.108
But it ain't up to me.

05:58.220 --> 05:59.824
Who's it up to?

05:59.940 --> 06:01.669
Fella in the wagon.

06:01.780 --> 06:04.226
Fella in the wagon ain't partial to company?

06:04.340 --> 06:06.547
Fella in the wagon,
he paid for a private trip,

06:06.660 --> 06:10.183
and I'm here to tell you,
he paid a pretty penny for privacy.

06:10.300 --> 06:13.110
So if you want to go to Minnie's with us,

06:13.220 --> 06:15.427
you gonna have to talk to him.

06:15.540 --> 06:18.020
Well...

06:18.140 --> 06:20.427
that's what I'll do.

06:21.980 --> 06:25.029
- (GUN COCKS)
- MAN: Hold it, black fella.

06:25.140 --> 06:28.508
'Fore you approach,
you take them two guns of yours

06:28.620 --> 06:31.863
and you lay 'em on that rock over yonder.

06:31.980 --> 06:36.463
Then you raise both your hands
way above your hat.

06:36.580 --> 06:38.742
Then you approach.

06:38.860 --> 06:40.305
Molasses-like.

06:41.420 --> 06:43.502
Real trustin' fella, huh?

06:43.620 --> 06:45.463
Not so much.

06:49.340 --> 06:51.707
(HORSES SNORT QUIETLY)

06:53.500 --> 06:55.468
(BIRDS CAWING)

06:57.940 --> 06:59.988
MAN: Put 'em down.

07:08.620 --> 07:10.509
Come on ahead.

07:10.620 --> 07:13.988
I said way above your hat, goddamn it!

07:15.380 --> 07:18.031
Now come forward.

07:18.180 --> 07:19.944
That's far enough.

07:20.100 --> 07:22.421
(CHAINS JINGLING)

07:25.940 --> 07:27.829
(CHUCKLING): Well, I'll be dogged.

07:27.980 --> 07:29.744
You a black fella I know.

07:29.900 --> 07:32.187
Colonel somethin'-or-other Warren, right?

07:32.300 --> 07:35.224
Major Marquis Warren.

07:35.340 --> 07:37.104
I know you, too.

07:37.220 --> 07:41.268
We, uh, shared a steak dinner
once upon a time in Chattanooga.

07:41.380 --> 07:43.189
You John Ruth The Hangman.

07:43.300 --> 07:44.790
That'd be me.

07:44.900 --> 07:46.106
How long's that been?

07:46.220 --> 07:47.631
Since that steak?

07:47.740 --> 07:50.869
Oh... eight months.

07:50.980 --> 07:53.460
So why don't you explain to me

07:53.580 --> 07:55.662
what a African bounty hunter's doin'

07:55.780 --> 07:58.943
wanderin' around in the snow
in the middle of Wyoming?

07:59.060 --> 08:00.983
Trying to get a couple
of bounties in to Red Rock.

08:01.140 --> 08:02.301
So you still in business?

08:02.420 --> 08:03.865
(CHUCKLES): You know I am.

08:04.020 --> 08:05.784
Happened to your horse?

08:05.900 --> 08:09.188
Circumstances caused us to have
to take the long way round.

08:09.300 --> 08:11.223
- My horse couldn't make it.
- Mm.

08:11.340 --> 08:13.741
You don't know nothin' 'bout this filly here.

08:13.900 --> 08:15.311
Nope.

08:15.420 --> 08:17.707
- Don't even know her name?
- Nope.

08:17.820 --> 08:21.506
Well, I guess that makes this
one fortuitous wagon.

08:21.660 --> 08:23.583
I sure as hell hope so.

08:23.700 --> 08:27.261
Major Marquis Warren,
this here's Daisy Domergue.

08:28.780 --> 08:31.670
Domergue, to you this is Major Warren.

08:31.780 --> 08:33.270
Howdy, nigger.

08:33.419 --> 08:34.831
(JOHN CHUCKLES)

08:34.940 --> 08:36.783
She's a pepper, ain't she?

08:36.900 --> 08:40.020
Now, girl, don't you know the darkies
don't like being called niggers no more?

08:40.179 --> 08:41.385
They find it offensive.

08:41.500 --> 08:43.025
I been called worse.

08:43.179 --> 08:44.545
(LAUGHS): Now, that I can believe.

08:44.660 --> 08:46.071
You never heard of her, huh?

08:46.180 --> 08:47.511
Should I?

08:47.620 --> 08:49.190
Well, she ain't no John Wilkes Booth,

08:49.300 --> 08:53.143
but maybe you might heard tell
about the price on her head.

08:53.260 --> 08:55.024
- WARREN: How much?
- $10,000.

08:55.140 --> 08:56.710
Damn.

08:56.860 --> 08:59.181
What'd she do, kill Lily Langtry?

08:59.300 --> 09:00.904
(CHUCKLES): Not quite.

09:01.020 --> 09:03.910
That ten thousand's practically in my pocket.

09:04.020 --> 09:07.388
It's why I ain't too anxious
to be handin' out rides,

09:07.540 --> 09:09.941
especially to professionals
open for business.

09:10.060 --> 09:11.585
I can certainly appreciate that.

09:11.700 --> 09:14.544
But I ain't got no designs on her.

09:14.660 --> 09:17.311
One of my fellas over there is worth $4,000,

09:17.420 --> 09:20.469
another one's worth $3,000,
and one of 'em's worth $1,000.

09:20.580 --> 09:22.025
That's damn sure good enough for me.

09:22.180 --> 09:26.185
(CHUCKLES)
Well... let me see their paperwork.

09:26.300 --> 09:29.543
Like I said, molasses-like.

09:32.260 --> 09:34.342
(JOHN SIGHS)

09:38.300 --> 09:39.381
Back off.

09:44.700 --> 09:47.749
(CHAINS JINGLING)

09:47.860 --> 09:50.067
(JOHN SIGHS)

09:50.180 --> 09:51.784
(SNIFFS)

09:59.620 --> 10:01.987
(SNIFFING)

10:02.980 --> 10:05.586
(JOHN MUMBLING)

10:05.700 --> 10:08.271
- (WARREN LAUGHS SOFTLY)
- (HORSES WHINNYING)

10:08.380 --> 10:10.428
DRIVER: Look, I sure hate
to interrupt you all,

10:10.540 --> 10:14.181
but we got a cold damn blizzard
that's hot on our ass

10:14.300 --> 10:16.109
that we're tryin' to beat to shelter!

10:16.220 --> 10:18.621
I realize that! Now, shut your mouth

10:18.740 --> 10:21.346
and hold them damn horses while I think!

10:21.460 --> 10:23.906
(HUFFS LOUDLY)

10:24.020 --> 10:26.466
Okay, boy, we'll give it a try.

10:26.620 --> 10:29.829
But you leave them two pistols
over yonder with the driver.

10:32.820 --> 10:36.671
DOMERGUE: Hey, uh, you ain't really
gonna let that nigger ride in here, is ya?

10:36.780 --> 10:38.145
I mean, maybe up there with O.B., but...

10:38.260 --> 10:40.183
- (THUD)
- (DOMERGUE CRIES OUT)

10:40.340 --> 10:42.627
JOHN: How ya like the sound
of them bells, bitch?

10:42.740 --> 10:44.105
They real pretty, ain't they?

10:44.260 --> 10:45.500
(CHUCKLING)

10:45.620 --> 10:49.384
You open up your trashy mouth again,
I'll knock out them front teeth for ya.

10:49.500 --> 10:51.502
- You got it?
- (WIND WHISTLING)

10:51.620 --> 10:53.384
(QUIETLY): Yeah.

10:53.500 --> 10:55.628
Let me hear ya say, "I got it."

10:55.740 --> 10:57.424
(LABORED BREATHING)

10:57.540 --> 11:00.191
I got it.

11:00.300 --> 11:03.543
Uh, I'm gonna need a hand tyin'
these fellas up on the roof.

11:03.660 --> 11:06.231
Give O.B. $50 when we get to Red Rock.

11:06.340 --> 11:07.341
He'll help ya.

11:07.460 --> 11:08.985
Well, I agree with O.B.

11:09.100 --> 11:10.750
This storm got me concerned.

11:10.860 --> 11:13.022
We get goin' a lot quicker
you helped out, too.

11:13.140 --> 11:16.064
Goddamn it to hell,
I'm already regrettin' this.

11:16.180 --> 11:20.670
Now, I can't likely help you tie fellas
to the roof with my wrist cuffed to hers.

11:20.780 --> 11:22.589
And my wrist is gonna stay cuffed to hers,

11:22.700 --> 11:24.702
and she ain't never gonna
leave my goddamn side

11:24.820 --> 11:27.664
till I personally put her
in the Red Rock jail!

11:27.780 --> 11:29.430
Now, do you got that?

11:29.540 --> 11:31.190
Yeah, I got it.

11:31.300 --> 11:32.745
Good.

11:32.860 --> 11:35.227
(CHAIN JINGLING)

11:35.340 --> 11:36.990
O.B.: Get in, Dude!

11:37.100 --> 11:38.511
Hut! Get in!

11:38.620 --> 11:41.385
Go on! Hut!

11:41.500 --> 11:42.865
Come on!

11:42.980 --> 11:46.541
Dude, Coconut, giddyup.

11:46.700 --> 11:48.031
Yah!

11:48.140 --> 11:50.507
(♪♪♪)

11:56.580 --> 11:58.947
(♪♪♪)

12:14.620 --> 12:17.021
Hut!

12:21.580 --> 12:23.708
Giddyup!

12:25.020 --> 12:27.387
Yah! Cimarron! Leche! Get in!

12:27.500 --> 12:29.468
So, what happened to your horse?

12:29.580 --> 12:31.105
O.B.: Get in!

12:31.220 --> 12:32.984
He was kinda old.

12:33.100 --> 12:35.785
I done had him for a bit.

12:35.900 --> 12:37.948
When the weather took a turn for the worse,

12:38.060 --> 12:41.064
well, he done what he could,
but he couldn't make it.

12:41.180 --> 12:43.501
- O.B.: Get in!
- That's too bad.

12:43.620 --> 12:45.827
Yeah, it is.

12:45.940 --> 12:48.989
Me and ol' Lash done rode
a lot of miles together.

12:49.100 --> 12:51.023
Could say he was my best friend,

12:51.180 --> 12:55.265
if I considered stupid animals
friends, which I don't.

12:55.380 --> 12:57.826
Nevertheless, I'm gonna miss him.

12:59.460 --> 13:01.508
O.B.: Leche! Ha!

13:01.620 --> 13:03.782
WARREN: Who's this Daisy Domergue?

13:03.940 --> 13:06.591
A no damn good murdering bitch, that's who.

13:06.700 --> 13:08.304
O.B.: Come on, boys! Get up!

13:08.420 --> 13:11.510
I see you ain't got mixed emotions
about bringing a woman to a rope.

13:11.660 --> 13:14.470
By "woman," you mean her?

13:14.620 --> 13:17.100
No, I do not have mixed emotions.

13:17.220 --> 13:18.551
O.B.: Get in! Ha!

13:18.660 --> 13:20.822
So you taking her into Red Rock to hang.

13:20.940 --> 13:22.146
You bet.

13:22.260 --> 13:23.546
You gonna wait round to watch it?

13:23.660 --> 13:25.105
(CHUCKLES): Oh, you know I am.

13:25.220 --> 13:27.382
- O.B.: Come on!
- I want to hear her neck snap

13:27.500 --> 13:28.831
with my own two ears.

13:28.940 --> 13:30.669
O.B.: Get up, boys!

13:30.780 --> 13:33.226
- You never wait to watch 'em hang?
- Get up!

13:33.340 --> 13:37.661
My bounties never hang,
'cause I never bring 'em in alive.

13:37.780 --> 13:40.101
- Never?
- Never ever.

13:40.220 --> 13:41.631
- O.B.: Ha! Get up! Yah!
- We talked about this

13:41.740 --> 13:44.220
in Chattanooga. Bringing
desperate men in alive's

13:44.340 --> 13:45.785
a good way to get yourself dead.

13:45.940 --> 13:47.829
- O.B.: Get in there!
- Can't catch me sleeping

13:47.940 --> 13:49.226
if I don't close my eyes.

13:49.340 --> 13:50.751
I don't want to work that hard.

13:50.860 --> 13:52.703
No one said the job is supposed to be easy.

13:52.820 --> 13:54.868
No one said it's supposed to be
that hard, neither.

13:54.980 --> 13:57.870
- O.B.: Get up, boys! Ha!
- But that, little lady,

13:57.980 --> 13:59.869
is why they call him "The Hangman."

13:59.980 --> 14:02.551
When the handbill says "dead or alive,"

14:02.660 --> 14:06.150
the rest of us shoot ya in the back
from up on top of a perch somewhere,

14:06.260 --> 14:08.024
- bring ya in dead over a saddle.
- O.B.: Get in!

14:08.140 --> 14:11.826
But when John Ruth The Hangman catches ya,

14:11.940 --> 14:13.942
you don't die from no bullet in the back.

14:14.060 --> 14:15.664
Mm-mm.

14:15.780 --> 14:18.545
When The Hangman catches you, you hang.

14:18.660 --> 14:21.584
O.B.: Ha!

14:21.700 --> 14:23.828
You overrate him, nigger.

14:23.980 --> 14:27.587
I give ya he got guts,
but in the brains department,

14:27.700 --> 14:31.500
he like a man who took
a high dive in a low well.

14:31.620 --> 14:32.860
(JOHN LAUGHS)

14:32.980 --> 14:35.187
(DOMERGUE GROANING)

14:35.300 --> 14:37.189
- Now, Daisy,
- (SCREAMS)

14:37.300 --> 14:41.021
I want us to work out a signal
system of communication.

14:41.140 --> 14:46.431
When I elbow you real hard in
the face, that means "shut up."

14:46.540 --> 14:47.951
You got it?

14:49.140 --> 14:50.869
I got it.

14:50.980 --> 14:54.780
- (JOHN AND WARREN LAUGH)
- O.B.: Get in there!

14:57.700 --> 14:59.828
Come on now, boys, get in!

15:02.420 --> 15:03.785
(CLICKS TONGUE)

15:03.900 --> 15:05.868
(♪♪♪)

15:07.900 --> 15:11.621
♪ Hey, little apple blossom ♪

15:11.780 --> 15:16.547
♪ What seems to be the problem? ♪

15:16.700 --> 15:19.988
♪ All the ones you tell your troubles to ♪

15:20.100 --> 15:24.150
♪ They don't really care for you ♪

15:24.260 --> 15:27.469
♪ Come and tell me what you're thinking ♪

15:27.580 --> 15:32.029
♪ 'Cause just when the boat is sinking ♪

15:32.140 --> 15:35.462
♪ A little light is blinking ♪

15:35.580 --> 15:39.585
♪ And I will come and rescue you ♪

15:39.700 --> 15:43.341
♪ Lots of girls walk around in tears ♪

15:43.460 --> 15:47.101
♪ But that's not for you ♪

15:47.220 --> 15:49.951
♪ You've been looking all around for years ♪

15:50.060 --> 15:54.145
- ♪ For someone to tell your troubles to ♪
- Ha!

15:54.260 --> 15:58.151
♪ Come and sit with me and talk a while ♪

15:58.260 --> 16:02.106
♪ Let me see your pretty little smile ♪

16:02.220 --> 16:05.190
♪ Put your troubles in a little pile ♪

16:05.300 --> 16:08.941
♪ And I will sort them out
for you, all right. ♪

16:12.060 --> 16:14.108
- O.B.: Hyah!
- (REINS CRACKING)

16:14.220 --> 16:15.187
Get in!

16:15.340 --> 16:16.705
(SNIFFS)

16:20.060 --> 16:21.391
O.B.: Get in there!

16:26.420 --> 16:29.151
Mm.

16:29.260 --> 16:30.989
O.B.: Giddyup!

16:31.100 --> 16:33.546
(SNIFFS, SIGHS)

16:33.660 --> 16:37.460
I, uh... I know we only
met each other the once before,

16:37.580 --> 16:41.062
- and I don't mean to unduly imply intimacy,
- Get up!

16:41.180 --> 16:44.901
- ...but, well...
- Yah!

16:45.020 --> 16:47.022
...you still got it?

16:47.140 --> 16:48.346
Do I still got what?

16:48.500 --> 16:49.911
O.B.: Get in, now!

16:50.020 --> 16:52.148
The Lincoln letter.

16:52.260 --> 16:53.910
Mm. Course.

16:54.020 --> 16:56.341
O.B.: Get up, boys!

16:56.460 --> 16:57.985
- Got it on ya?
- Mm-hmm.

16:58.100 --> 16:58.987
O.B.: Come on!

16:59.100 --> 17:00.067
Where?

17:00.220 --> 17:01.904
Right here.

17:02.020 --> 17:03.670
O.B.: Come on, boys! Get up!

17:03.780 --> 17:05.987
Look, I know you got to be
real careful with it and all,

17:06.140 --> 17:08.825
and I can imagine you probably
don't like taking it

17:08.980 --> 17:10.789
in and out of the envelope all that often,

17:10.940 --> 17:12.782
- but, uh...
- Get up!

17:12.940 --> 17:16.830
...if you wouldn't mind, I'd sure
appreciate seeing that again.

17:16.940 --> 17:18.385
O.B.: Get in, boys!

17:18.500 --> 17:21.663
Ha! Giddyup!

17:21.780 --> 17:23.020
You're right.

17:23.140 --> 17:25.268
I don't like taking it in and out

17:25.380 --> 17:27.541
- of the envelope that much.
- I... Yeah.

17:27.660 --> 17:29.025
- But...
- Get in!

17:29.140 --> 17:32.030
...seeing's how you saved my life and all...

17:32.140 --> 17:34.222
I suppose I could let you read it again.

17:34.380 --> 17:36.428
O.B.: Get in! Ha!

17:36.540 --> 17:39.020
Get in there!

17:41.260 --> 17:43.228
Get up now!

17:49.100 --> 17:50.545
Get in!

17:50.660 --> 17:52.071
Giddyup!

17:52.180 --> 17:54.148
Huh!

17:58.300 --> 18:00.428
Get in, now!

18:04.700 --> 18:06.384
Get in!

18:06.500 --> 18:08.468
(WIND WHISTLING)

18:15.020 --> 18:17.102
(CLICKS TONGUE)

18:17.220 --> 18:21.225
"Ole Mary Todd's calling,
so I guess it must be time for bed."

18:23.260 --> 18:25.149
Ole Mary Todd.

18:25.260 --> 18:27.706
O.B.: Ha!

18:27.820 --> 18:30.107
Get in!

18:30.220 --> 18:32.461
- Well, that...
- Get up, boys!

18:32.580 --> 18:33.467
...that gets me.

18:33.580 --> 18:34.706
(CHUCKLES)

18:34.820 --> 18:36.788
Yeah, it gets me, too.

18:36.940 --> 18:38.749
O.B.: Get in! Get in!

18:38.900 --> 18:41.949
You know what this is, tramp? Hmm?

18:42.060 --> 18:44.301
It's a letter from Lincoln.

18:44.420 --> 18:46.900
- Letter from Lincoln to him.
- Get in there!

18:47.020 --> 18:48.306
Yeah.

18:48.420 --> 18:50.388
They shared a correspondence during the war.

18:50.540 --> 18:51.905
They was pen pals.

18:52.020 --> 18:54.910
- And this is just one of the letters.
- Get up!

18:57.580 --> 18:59.344
What the...

18:59.460 --> 19:01.508
- Hyah!
- WARREN: O.B.!

19:01.620 --> 19:02.906
Stop!

19:03.020 --> 19:03.987
O.B.: Whoa!

19:04.100 --> 19:05.181
Easy.

19:05.300 --> 19:06.631
Whoa.

19:06.740 --> 19:08.708
(BOTH GROANING)

19:10.500 --> 19:12.867
(GROANS) All the stupid...

19:13.020 --> 19:15.466
Like to rip my goddamn arm off!

19:15.580 --> 19:18.470
(JOHN COUGHING)

19:18.580 --> 19:20.548
(GROANING)

19:22.660 --> 19:24.628
(GRUNTING)

19:39.660 --> 19:41.071
(WARREN SPITS)

19:41.180 --> 19:43.342
(JOHN GROANS)

19:43.460 --> 19:44.507
(DOMERGUE GROANS)

19:44.620 --> 19:46.861
(JOHN PANTING)

19:48.940 --> 19:52.581
I didn't drag her stinking ass
up this goddamn mountain

19:52.700 --> 19:55.021
just for you to break her neck
on the outskirts of town!

19:55.140 --> 19:57.711
You the one handed her my goddamn letter!

19:57.820 --> 20:01.428
- I didn't give it to her, I give it to you!
- (SPITS)

20:03.660 --> 20:05.788
That nigger like to bust my jaw.

20:05.900 --> 20:06.981
(CHUCKLES)

20:08.820 --> 20:12.348
You ruin that letter of his, that nigger
gonna stomp your ass to death.

20:12.460 --> 20:16.981
And when he do, I'm gonna sit back on
that wagon wheel, watch and laugh!

20:17.100 --> 20:17.987
(PANTING)

20:18.100 --> 20:19.864
How is it?

20:19.980 --> 20:21.823
Well, she ain't help it none.

20:21.940 --> 20:23.783
But it's all right.

20:23.900 --> 20:27.621
Is that the way niggers treat their ladies?

20:27.740 --> 20:30.220
You ain't no goddamn lady!

20:30.340 --> 20:31.671
(SCREAMS)

20:37.340 --> 20:38.785
O.B.: Hey, Mr. Ruth!

20:38.940 --> 20:40.510
What?

20:40.620 --> 20:42.907
There's another fella on foot
up here on the road.

20:43.020 --> 20:45.261
MAN (IN DISTANCE): Hey!

20:45.380 --> 20:47.223
What?

20:47.340 --> 20:52.301
I said there's another fella
on foot, up here on the road.

20:57.140 --> 20:59.108
(WIND WHISTLING)

21:03.580 --> 21:05.548
(PANTING)

21:09.420 --> 21:12.310
MAN: Hey! Hey!

21:12.420 --> 21:15.185
Considering there's a blizzard going on,

21:15.300 --> 21:18.510
whole lot of fellas walking around,
wouldn't you say, Major?

21:18.620 --> 21:20.509
Well, seeing as how I'm half of them fellas,

21:20.620 --> 21:22.827
uh, yeah, seems to be a lot of us.

21:22.980 --> 21:26.826
This changes things, son.

21:26.940 --> 21:30.422
$8,000 a lot of money for a nigger.

21:30.540 --> 21:32.702
With a partner, 18's a whole lot better.

21:32.820 --> 21:36.267
You really think I'm in cahoots
with that fella, or her?

21:36.380 --> 21:37.711
Put them on.

21:37.820 --> 21:39.151
Oh, I ain't wearing no handcuffs.

21:39.260 --> 21:43.621
You put those on, or you can stop
worrying about this whole thing right now!

21:44.780 --> 21:46.384
MAN: Hey!

21:57.780 --> 22:00.670
MAN: Hey!

22:04.420 --> 22:06.309
(WIND WHISTLING)

22:06.420 --> 22:08.900
JOHN: Hand your weapons to the driver.

22:09.020 --> 22:10.909
Little jumpy, ain't you?

22:11.020 --> 22:13.910
Never mind the jokes. Just do it.

22:14.020 --> 22:15.465
If you say so.

22:15.620 --> 22:17.588
I do.

22:39.460 --> 22:41.349
Okay.

22:41.460 --> 22:42.825
I done done it.

22:42.980 --> 22:44.709
O.B., you got 'em?

22:44.820 --> 22:45.821
I got 'em.

22:45.980 --> 22:47.709
Okay, fella.

22:47.860 --> 22:50.227
You keep holding that lantern
in that one hand,

22:50.340 --> 22:53.469
and you keep that other hand
where I can see it.

22:53.580 --> 22:56.311
Walk over there where I can
get a good look at ya.

23:08.500 --> 23:12.300
Well, I'll be a goddamn dog in a manger.

23:12.420 --> 23:15.185
Is that you, Chris Mannix?

23:15.300 --> 23:17.189
I'm sorry, friend, do we know each other?

23:17.300 --> 23:18.301
Not quite.

23:18.420 --> 23:19.706
You know this fella?

23:19.820 --> 23:21.948
Only by reputation.

23:22.100 --> 23:26.105
Like I said, friend, you got me
at a bit of a disadvantage.

23:26.220 --> 23:29.902
Keeping you at a disadvantage
is an advantage I intend to keep.

23:30.020 --> 23:33.024
Uh, whoever you are, mister,
you sure sound tough

23:33.140 --> 23:36.223
when you talking to a desperate
man knee-deep in snow.

23:36.340 --> 23:38.820
I... I don't want no trouble.

23:38.940 --> 23:40.021
I just want a ride.

23:40.140 --> 23:42.381
I'm freezing to death!

23:42.540 --> 23:44.030
Who is this joker?

23:44.140 --> 23:48.748
You heard of the rebel renegade
Erskine Mannix?

23:48.860 --> 23:50.828
- Mannix's Marauders?
- That's them.

23:50.940 --> 23:53.989
Scourge of South Carolina,
Mannix's Marauders.

23:54.100 --> 23:56.421
It's Erskine's youngest boy, Chris.

23:56.540 --> 23:58.781
Brings you in my path, Chris Mannix?

23:58.900 --> 24:02.302
Well, Mr. Face, I was riding to Red Rock,

24:02.420 --> 24:04.787
my horse stepped in
a gopher hole in the snow,

24:04.900 --> 24:07.221
fucked up his leg, had to put 'er down.

24:07.340 --> 24:08.785
You got business in Red Rock?

24:08.940 --> 24:10.430
- Yes, I do.
- What?

24:10.540 --> 24:12.144
I'm the new sheriff.

24:12.260 --> 24:13.785
(SCOFFS): Horseshit.

24:13.900 --> 24:15.789
- 'Fraid not.
- Where's your star?

24:15.900 --> 24:17.504
Well, I ain't the sheriff yet.

24:17.620 --> 24:19.429
Now, once I get there, they swear me in.

24:19.540 --> 24:21.190
But, uh, that ain't happened yet.

24:21.300 --> 24:22.825
And that's when you get your star.

24:22.940 --> 24:25.102
You got anything that can
back any of this up?

24:25.220 --> 24:27.461
Yeah. When we get to Red Rock.

24:27.580 --> 24:30.550
And from the look of those
three frozen fuckers up there,

24:30.660 --> 24:33.186
I figure you a bounty hunter
open for business.

24:33.340 --> 24:37.342
And I figure you taking them three
dead bodies into Red Rock to get paid?

24:37.460 --> 24:38.621
Three dead.

24:38.740 --> 24:39.627
One alive.

24:39.740 --> 24:40.662
(CHAINS CLINK)

24:40.780 --> 24:41.667
CHRIS: Who's that?

24:41.780 --> 24:43.464
JOHN: Daisy Domergue.

24:43.580 --> 24:45.628
Who the fuck is Daisy Domergue?

24:45.740 --> 24:49.267
Not a goddamn thing to nobody,
except me and the hangman.

24:49.380 --> 24:50.666
The hangman?

24:53.220 --> 24:56.508
Well, I'll be double-dog damned.

24:56.620 --> 24:58.145
You're "The Hangman" Bob Ruth!

24:58.260 --> 24:59.386
It's John.

24:59.500 --> 25:01.741
And you!

25:01.860 --> 25:03.510
You're the nigger with the head!

25:03.660 --> 25:05.662
Major Marquis!

25:05.780 --> 25:10.261
My Lord, is that really the real head
of Major Marquis looking at me now?

25:10.420 --> 25:12.866
Yeah, it's really me,
and it's really my head.

25:12.980 --> 25:14.664
So what's going on?

25:14.780 --> 25:16.509
Uh, y'all having a bounty hunters' picnic?

25:16.620 --> 25:18.065
Never mind.

25:18.180 --> 25:19.909
Uh, you taking them three dead bodies

25:20.020 --> 25:21.909
and hurrying to Red Rock
to get paid, ain't you?

25:22.020 --> 25:23.260
Yeah.

25:23.380 --> 25:24.745
Well, the man in Red Rock's

25:24.860 --> 25:28.501
supposed to pay you is me, the new sheriff.

25:28.620 --> 25:32.502
So if y'all want to get paid,
y'all need to get me to Red Rock.

25:32.620 --> 25:34.509
Well, excuse me
for finding it hard to believe

25:34.620 --> 25:38.181
a town electing you to do
anything except drop dead.

25:38.300 --> 25:42.227
So I'm supposed to freeze to death
'cause you find something hard to believe?

25:44.300 --> 25:45.870
(SIGHS)

25:45.980 --> 25:47.903
No, I suppose not.

25:52.740 --> 25:54.708
Put them on and come inside.

26:01.700 --> 26:03.543
No.

26:07.180 --> 26:08.625
Then you'll freeze.

26:08.740 --> 26:10.390
Then you'll hang.

26:10.500 --> 26:12.548
(CHUCKLES) How so?

26:12.660 --> 26:16.745
Stagecoach driver, could you
come down here and join us?

26:16.900 --> 26:18.345
I got to hold these horses.

26:18.460 --> 26:20.588
I can hear you just fine from up here.

26:20.740 --> 26:22.583
Well, you just heard me tell this fella

26:22.740 --> 26:25.949
I'm the new sheriff of Red Rock, right?

26:26.060 --> 26:26.982
O.B.: Yeah.

26:27.100 --> 26:29.580
Red Rock is my town now.

26:29.700 --> 26:32.101
And I'm gonna enter my town
in bounty hunter's chains?

26:32.220 --> 26:33.585
No, sir!

26:33.700 --> 26:37.342
Sorry, bushwhackers,
I ain't entering Red Rock that way.

26:37.460 --> 26:39.189
Now, when you finally get to Red Rock,

26:39.340 --> 26:42.230
you gonna realize every
goddamn thing I said was right.

26:42.340 --> 26:44.627
And I expect you, O.B.,

26:44.740 --> 26:47.141
to tell the townsfolk of Red Rock

26:47.260 --> 26:50.104
that John Ruth let their
new sheriff freeze to death.

26:50.220 --> 26:52.109
Ain't no bounty on my head, bushwhacker.

26:52.220 --> 26:55.303
You let me die, that's murder.

26:58.900 --> 27:00.868
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

27:03.420 --> 27:05.388
JOHN: Hold out your hands.

27:07.100 --> 27:08.989
O.B.!

27:09.100 --> 27:11.068
Give the major back his iron.

27:12.780 --> 27:16.344
One thing I know for sure,
this nigger-hating son of a gun

27:16.500 --> 27:18.628
ain't partnered up with you.

27:18.740 --> 27:21.823
Now, I'll help you protect your 8,000,

27:21.940 --> 27:23.988
you help me protect my ten.

27:24.100 --> 27:25.784
Deal?

27:27.340 --> 27:29.229
Well, ain't love grand?

27:29.340 --> 27:31.820
Y'all want to lie on the ground
and make snow angels together?

27:31.940 --> 27:33.704
(LAUGHS)

27:33.820 --> 27:34.901
O.B.: Hut!

27:35.060 --> 27:37.222
Come on!

27:37.340 --> 27:39.308
Hyah!

27:40.540 --> 27:42.986
(CHRIS WHOOPING)

27:43.100 --> 27:44.625
CHRIS: Well, I'll tell you what, Bob.

27:44.780 --> 27:46.020
JOHN: The name's John.

27:46.140 --> 27:47.665
- When we get to Red Rock,
- O.B.: Hyah!

27:47.780 --> 27:49.350
I'll buy you and Major Marquis there

27:49.460 --> 27:50.825
- dinner and booze.
- O.B.: Get in!

27:50.940 --> 27:52.226
My way of saying thanks.

27:52.340 --> 27:54.707
I don't drink with rebel renegades,

27:54.820 --> 27:57.266
and I damn sure don't break bread with them.

27:57.420 --> 27:59.468
- Well, Mr. Ruth...
- O.B.: Get up, boys!

27:59.580 --> 28:02.670
...you sound like you got a axe
to grind against the Cause.

28:02.780 --> 28:05.704
- "The Cause" of a renegade army?
- O.B.: Get in!

28:05.820 --> 28:07.868
Bunch of losers gone loco.

28:07.980 --> 28:09.709
- You bet I do.
- O.B.: Get up there! Hyah!

28:09.820 --> 28:12.985
You wrapped yourselves up in a rebel
flag as an excuse to kill and steal.

28:13.140 --> 28:15.507
And this ought to interest you, Warren.

28:15.620 --> 28:18.021
Imparticular, emancipated blacks.

28:18.140 --> 28:19.710
Sounds like my kind of fella.

28:19.820 --> 28:20.981
(JOHN GROANS)

28:22.220 --> 28:23.824
Sound to me you been reading

28:23.940 --> 28:27.740
a lot of newspapers printed
in Washington, D.C.

28:27.860 --> 28:30.830
- O.B.: Get in! Huh!
- CHRIS: Anywho, I'm just trying

28:30.940 --> 28:33.022
to let y'all know how grateful I am.

28:33.140 --> 28:34.710
I was a goner.

28:34.820 --> 28:36.185
And y'all saved me.

28:36.300 --> 28:38.621
You want to show me how grateful you are?

28:38.740 --> 28:40.504
- O.B.: Get in there!
- Shut up.

28:40.620 --> 28:41.985
(WARREN LAUGHS)

28:42.100 --> 28:43.226
- (CHAINS JINGLING)
- JOHN: Goddamn it, Daisy.

28:43.380 --> 28:46.304
It's coming.

28:46.420 --> 28:47.751
O.B.: Get in there, Cimarron!

28:47.860 --> 28:49.021
Here.

28:49.180 --> 28:50.067
Last piece.

28:50.220 --> 28:52.951
O.B.: Get in!

28:53.100 --> 28:55.387
Get in, now!

28:55.500 --> 28:57.582
Hyah!

28:57.700 --> 28:59.543
(WHISPERING): Does he know...

28:59.660 --> 29:01.310
(CHRIS SIGHS)

29:01.420 --> 29:04.344
Does he know how famous you once was?

29:04.460 --> 29:05.700
I don't think so.

29:05.860 --> 29:07.385
O.B.: Giddyup!

29:07.500 --> 29:09.150
Black Eye.

29:10.780 --> 29:12.270
- Do you know who he is?
- O.B.: Get in!

29:12.380 --> 29:14.860
Do I know about the $30,000 reward

29:14.980 --> 29:17.301
the Confederacy put on the head
of Major Marquis?

29:17.420 --> 29:19.024
- O.B.: Come on now, boys!
- (DOMERGUE CHUCKLES)

29:19.140 --> 29:20.585
- O.B.: Get in!
- Yeah.

29:20.700 --> 29:22.543
Ah, them hillbillies
went nigger head-hunting.

29:22.660 --> 29:24.264
- O.B.: Get in!
- They just never did get 'em

29:24.420 --> 29:25.546
the right nigger head, did they?

29:25.660 --> 29:27.583
No, they didn't.

29:27.700 --> 29:29.111
But it wasn't for lack of trying.

29:29.260 --> 29:30.785
O.B.: Get in, boys! Ha! Get on!

29:30.900 --> 29:32.664
Them peckerwoods
left their homes and families,

29:32.780 --> 29:35.624
and come up this snowy mountain
looking for me and fortune.

29:35.740 --> 29:37.549
O.B.: Ha! Get up!

29:37.660 --> 29:39.264
Ain't none of 'em found fortune.

29:39.380 --> 29:42.304
The ones you ain't never heard of no more,

29:42.420 --> 29:44.184
they found me.

29:44.300 --> 29:46.507
Now, it didn't stay $30,000
the length of the war.

29:46.620 --> 29:49.465
Once passions cooled,
it dropped down to eight, then five.

29:49.580 --> 29:50.786
O.B.: Get up, boys! Ha!

29:50.900 --> 29:53.028
But I bet even when it was 5,000,

29:53.140 --> 29:55.791
you had your share
of country boys coming to call.

29:55.900 --> 29:59.029
(CHUCKLES) Mm, you know I did.

29:59.140 --> 30:01.791
Why'd they have a reward on you?

30:01.900 --> 30:04.301
Confederates took exception
to my capacity for killing 'em.

30:04.460 --> 30:05.825
- (CHRIS LAUGHS)
- O.B.: Get up, now!

30:05.940 --> 30:08.022
And after I broke out of Wellenbeck,

30:08.140 --> 30:10.905
well, the South took my continued existence

30:11.020 --> 30:12.784
- as a personal affront.
- O.B.: Get up!

30:12.900 --> 30:15.790
- And the Cause put a reward on my head.
- JOHN: Hmm.

30:15.900 --> 30:16.947
O.B.: Get in there!

30:17.100 --> 30:19.580
What's, uh, Wellenbeck?

30:19.700 --> 30:22.705
You ain't never heard of Wellenbeck
prisoner of war camp, West Virginia?

30:22.820 --> 30:24.663
No, reb, I ain't never heard of it.

30:24.780 --> 30:26.623
- O.B.: Hyah!
- Did you bust out?

30:26.740 --> 30:28.185
Oh,

30:28.300 --> 30:31.543
Major Marquis did more than bust out.

30:31.660 --> 30:33.389
Major Marquis had a bright idea.

30:33.500 --> 30:34.581
O.B.: Get in, now!

30:34.740 --> 30:37.027
So bright, you got to wonder

30:37.140 --> 30:39.461
why nobody never thought about it before.

30:40.980 --> 30:43.028
Tell John Ruth your bright idea.

30:43.140 --> 30:44.744
(CHUCKLES)

30:44.860 --> 30:48.705
Well, the whole damn place
was just made out of kindling.

30:48.820 --> 30:50.106
O.B.: Get in!

30:50.220 --> 30:51.710
So I burnt it down.

30:51.820 --> 30:52.981
(LAUGHTER)

30:54.260 --> 30:56.342
O.B.: Get in! Hyah!

30:58.220 --> 31:01.747
There was a rookie regiment
spending overnight in the camp.

31:01.860 --> 31:04.943
47 men burnt to a crisp.

31:05.060 --> 31:08.109
- Southern youth, farmers' sons,
- O.B.: Get up!

31:08.220 --> 31:09.346
...cream of the crop.

31:09.460 --> 31:11.064
And I say, "Let 'em burn."

31:11.180 --> 31:14.627
I'm supposed to apologize
for killing Johnny Reb?

31:14.780 --> 31:17.465
You joined the war to keep niggers in chains.

31:17.620 --> 31:19.463
I joined the war to kill

31:19.620 --> 31:21.190
- white Southern crackers.
- O.B.: Ha! Get up!

31:21.300 --> 31:23.348
And that means killing 'em any way I can.

31:23.500 --> 31:25.628
- O.B.: Get in!
- Shoot 'em, stab 'em,

31:25.740 --> 31:30.021
drown 'em, burn 'em,
drop a big ol' rock on their head.

31:30.140 --> 31:31.744
Whatever it took to put
white Southern crackers

31:31.860 --> 31:33.624
- in the ground,
- O.B.: Get up!

31:33.740 --> 31:35.504
...that's what I joined the war to do.

31:35.620 --> 31:36.860
And that's what I did.

31:36.980 --> 31:39.028
To answer your question, John Ruth,

31:39.180 --> 31:43.071
when Major Marquis burned 47 men alive,

31:43.180 --> 31:45.990
for no more reason than to give
a nigger a run for the trees,

31:46.100 --> 31:49.306
that's when the South put a reward
on the head of Major Marquis.

31:49.420 --> 31:51.184
- And I made them trees, Mannix.
- O.B.: Get in!

31:51.300 --> 31:54.904
You best believe I ain't looked back
till I crossed the Northern line.

31:55.020 --> 31:58.942
Oh, but you had a surprise waiting for
you on the Northern side, didn't you?

31:59.060 --> 32:03.420
See, once they started pulling out
all them burnt bodies at Wellenbeck,

32:03.580 --> 32:05.901
seems not all them boys were rebs.

32:06.020 --> 32:10.425
Why, you burn up some of your
own boys, didn't you, Major?

32:10.540 --> 32:12.907
How many burnt prisoners they end up finding?

32:13.020 --> 32:17.420
Wasn't the final Yankee death
count something like 37?

32:17.540 --> 32:18.905
- O.B.: Giddyup!
- (REINS CRACKING)

32:19.020 --> 32:20.704
That's the thing about war, Mannix.

32:20.820 --> 32:22.265
People die.

32:22.380 --> 32:23.711
Oh.

32:23.820 --> 32:26.903
So you gonna chalk it up
to "war is hell," huh?

32:27.060 --> 32:29.461
Well, admittedly, that is
a hard argument to argue with.

32:29.580 --> 32:31.469
But if memory serves,

32:31.580 --> 32:34.948
your side didn't look at it that way.

32:35.060 --> 32:37.461
I think they thought 37 white men

32:37.580 --> 32:39.947
for one nigger

32:40.060 --> 32:42.222
wasn't so hot a trade.

32:42.340 --> 32:45.628
- I do believe they accused you
- O.B.: Giddyup!

32:45.740 --> 32:47.026
...of being a kill-crazy nigger

32:47.140 --> 32:49.222
who only joined the war to kill white folks,

32:49.340 --> 32:52.147
and the whole blue and gray of it all
really didn't matter that much to you.

32:52.260 --> 32:53.705
O.B.: Ha! Get up!

32:53.820 --> 32:55.822
And that's why they drummed your black ass

32:55.940 --> 32:58.341
out of the cavalry with
a yellow stripe down your back.

32:58.460 --> 33:01.623
- O.B.: Get in!
- Isn't it, Major?

33:01.740 --> 33:03.105
Horseshit!

33:03.220 --> 33:04.665
If he'd have did all that, the cavalry

33:04.780 --> 33:06.191
- would've shot him.
- O.B.: Get in!

33:06.300 --> 33:07.790
Well, I didn't say they could prove it.

33:07.900 --> 33:09.265
- O.B.: Get up!
- But they sure did

33:09.380 --> 33:11.303
think it out loud, didn't they, Major?

33:11.420 --> 33:13.263
O.B.: Hyah! Get up, boys!

33:13.380 --> 33:16.031
But Warren's war record was stellar,

33:16.140 --> 33:18.507
and that's what saved his ass.

33:18.620 --> 33:19.781
O.B.: Hyah!

33:19.900 --> 33:21.709
Now, you killed yourself your share

33:21.820 --> 33:26.109
of redskins in your day,
didn't you, Black Major?

33:26.220 --> 33:28.222
Cavalry tends to look kindly on that.

33:28.340 --> 33:31.230
I'll tell you what the cavalry
didn't look kindly on.

33:31.340 --> 33:33.555
- O.B.: Giddyup!
- Mannix's Marauders, that's what.

33:33.656 --> 33:34.670
O.B.: Get in! Hyah!

33:34.780 --> 33:36.862
And the fact that Erskine Mannix's little boy

33:36.980 --> 33:38.869
would talk about anybody else's behavior

33:38.980 --> 33:42.382
during war time makes me want to horse-laugh.

33:42.500 --> 33:43.740
O.B.: Hyah!

33:43.860 --> 33:46.989
Don't you say anything about my daddy.

33:47.140 --> 33:50.508
- What he fought for was dignity in defeat,
- O.B.: Get up there!

33:50.620 --> 33:52.941
...and against the unconditional surrender.

33:53.060 --> 33:56.507
We weren't foreign barbarians
pounding on the city walls.

33:56.620 --> 33:58.622
- O.B.: Ha!
- We were your brothers.

33:58.780 --> 34:00.111
O.B.: Get up, now!

34:00.220 --> 34:02.029
We deserved dignity in defeat.

34:02.140 --> 34:04.905
WARREN: Just how many
nigger towns did y'all sack

34:05.020 --> 34:07.421
in your fight for dignity in defeat?

34:07.580 --> 34:09.867
Oh, my fair share, Black Major.

34:09.980 --> 34:12.585
- 'Cause when niggers are scared,
- O.B.: Huh!

34:12.699 --> 34:14.589
...that's when white folks are safe.

34:14.699 --> 34:16.190
(GUN CLICKS)

34:16.340 --> 34:19.184
You gonna talk that hateful nigger talk,

34:19.340 --> 34:22.549
you can ride up top with O.B.

34:22.659 --> 34:23.866
No.

34:23.980 --> 34:25.550
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

34:25.659 --> 34:28.139
You done got me talking politics.

34:28.260 --> 34:30.388
I didn't want to.

34:30.500 --> 34:33.549
Like I said, y'all,
I'm just happy to be alive.

34:33.659 --> 34:35.708
- (CHRIS CLEARS THROAT)
- O.B.: Get in, now!

34:35.860 --> 34:37.703
- (CHRIS SIGHS)
- O.B.: Ha! Get up!

34:37.860 --> 34:40.943
I think I'll scoot over here
right by this window,

34:41.060 --> 34:45.543
and let this beautiful carriage
rock me to sleep.

34:45.699 --> 34:48.465
And dream about how lucky I am.

34:48.620 --> 34:49.985
(CLEARS THROAT SOFTLY)

34:50.100 --> 34:52.068
(CLICKS)

34:52.179 --> 34:54.148
O.B.: Get up, now!

34:56.940 --> 34:59.625
O.B.: Ha!

34:59.740 --> 35:01.708
(♪♪♪)

35:14.100 --> 35:16.421
(WIND WHISTLING)

35:33.380 --> 35:35.747
(♪♪♪)

35:44.380 --> 35:46.109
Hyah! Get in!

35:46.260 --> 35:47.546
Get in there!

35:47.660 --> 35:48.900
Get in, hyah!

35:49.020 --> 35:50.226
Get in there!

35:50.340 --> 35:52.149
Get in!

35:52.260 --> 35:54.024
Get in there, Leche!

35:54.140 --> 35:55.949
Get in there!

35:56.060 --> 35:59.143
Whoa, whoa, easy.

35:59.260 --> 36:02.264
Whoa. Whoa.

36:04.540 --> 36:06.508
(WIND WHISTLING)

36:23.900 --> 36:25.504
What the hell is going on?

36:25.620 --> 36:28.544
We weren't expecting another stage tonight!

36:28.660 --> 36:32.710
Yeah, I can see you already
got another one up in here.

36:32.820 --> 36:35.471
Just got through putting the horses away.

36:35.580 --> 36:37.309
Well, this ain't the normal line,

36:37.420 --> 36:40.310
but we are stuck on
the wrong side of a blizzard,

36:40.420 --> 36:42.661
so it looks like you're stuck with us.

36:42.820 --> 36:44.788
Are Minnie and Sweet Dave inside?

36:44.900 --> 36:46.390
They ain't here.

36:46.500 --> 36:48.787
I'm running the place while they're gone.

36:48.900 --> 36:50.390
(WIND HOWLING)

36:50.500 --> 36:52.468
Where's Minnie and Sweet Dave?

36:52.620 --> 36:54.429
He says they ain't here.

36:54.580 --> 36:56.787
He's looking after the place
while they're gone.

36:56.900 --> 36:59.267
Who are you?

37:01.380 --> 37:02.586
I'm Bob.

37:04.900 --> 37:09.064
Well, whoever you are,
help O.B. with the horses.

37:09.220 --> 37:11.222
(GRUNTS) Come on.

37:11.340 --> 37:14.344
Get 'em out of this cold
'fore that blizzard hits us.

37:14.460 --> 37:16.940
Whoa. You all right?

37:17.100 --> 37:18.226
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait!

37:18.340 --> 37:19.387
Esperate, esperate, esperate!

37:19.500 --> 37:21.901
I just put those other horses away.

37:22.020 --> 37:25.069
You need it done fast, you need to help.

37:25.180 --> 37:27.660
I got two of my best men on it.

37:28.940 --> 37:31.227
You heard him, freeloaders.

37:31.340 --> 37:33.468
Get to work!

37:33.620 --> 37:36.100
BOB: All right, you two, unhook the leaders.

37:36.220 --> 37:37.506
Come on, let's go.

37:37.620 --> 37:39.224
JOHN: Open up!

37:39.340 --> 37:40.865
- MAN: You have to kick it open!
- MAN 2: Ya got to kick it open!

37:40.980 --> 37:41.867
DOMERGUE: What?

37:41.980 --> 37:43.470
Kick it open!

37:43.580 --> 37:45.389
- (WIND WHISTLING)
- Shut that door.

37:45.500 --> 37:46.661
There's a goddamn blizzard out there!

37:46.780 --> 37:48.145
You have to stop, close the door!

37:48.300 --> 37:49.540
You got to nail it shut.

37:49.660 --> 37:52.425
You have to, you have to nail it shut!

37:52.540 --> 37:53.905
Hold it shut!

37:54.020 --> 37:55.749
There's a hammer and nails by the door!

37:55.860 --> 37:57.271
You have to nail it shut!

37:57.380 --> 38:00.463
There's a hammer and nails by the door.

38:00.580 --> 38:02.469
- JOHN: Give me a hammer.
- DOMERGUE: Yeah.

38:02.580 --> 38:05.584
(GRUNTING)

38:11.380 --> 38:12.984
You need, you need two pieces of wood!

38:13.100 --> 38:14.829
You need two pieces of wood!
One ain't good enough!

38:14.940 --> 38:16.180
Two pieces of wood!

38:16.300 --> 38:18.667
The fuckin' thing is busted!

38:18.780 --> 38:21.511
Not just one piece of wood!

38:21.620 --> 38:25.028
- JOHN: Give me another piece of wood.
- DOMERGUE: Yeah. All right.

38:29.500 --> 38:31.104
- I need a nail.
- Here.

38:31.260 --> 38:33.467
(GRUNTING)

38:44.100 --> 38:45.670
Jesus.

38:45.780 --> 38:48.465
(PANTING)

38:48.580 --> 38:50.821
That door's a son of a gun.

38:50.940 --> 38:54.828
Who's the idiot who broke that,
that Mexican fella?

38:54.940 --> 38:56.305
Oh, good heavens.

38:56.420 --> 38:57.751
A woman?

38:57.860 --> 38:59.191
Out in this white hell?

38:59.300 --> 39:02.509
You must be frozen solid, poor thing.

39:02.620 --> 39:04.065
(JOHN GRUNTS)

39:04.180 --> 39:06.911
Looks like Minnie's got her a full house.

39:09.220 --> 39:11.348
When did you fellas arrive?

39:11.460 --> 39:12.507
Ah.

39:12.620 --> 39:14.543
About 40 minutes ago.

39:14.660 --> 39:16.424
That cowboy fella in the corner,

39:16.540 --> 39:18.463
- that your driver?
- No, no, he's a passenger.

39:18.580 --> 39:20.503
The driver lit out.

39:20.620 --> 39:23.621
Said he was going to spend the blizzard
shacked up with a friend.

39:23.740 --> 39:26.346
Lucky devil.

39:26.460 --> 39:28.588
Jesus Christ, that's awful!

39:28.700 --> 39:31.226
- (MAN CHUCKLES)
- Christ Almighty,

39:31.340 --> 39:34.344
what'd that Mexican fella do,
soak his old socks in a pot?

39:34.460 --> 39:37.066
Yes, uh... I think we all felt the same way,

39:37.180 --> 39:40.263
but were a little too polite
to say something.

39:40.380 --> 39:42.667
- He don't have that problem.
- Shit.

39:42.780 --> 39:44.464
Where's the well water?

39:44.580 --> 39:46.105
Uh, over there.

39:51.980 --> 39:55.507
So, all three of you fellas
headed to Red Rock

39:55.620 --> 39:58.385
when the blizzard stopped you, huh?

39:58.500 --> 40:01.663
Yes. All three of us were
on that stagecoach out there.

40:13.020 --> 40:15.591
(SNIFFS) Coffee beans.

40:15.740 --> 40:18.266
Uh, over there.

40:26.340 --> 40:28.547
Get your hand out of there.

40:32.540 --> 40:35.271
New sheriff of Red Rock's travelin' with us.

40:35.380 --> 40:38.270
Ah, sheriff of Red Rock, that'll be the day.

40:38.380 --> 40:41.224
He's a goddamn sheriff, I'm a monkey's uncle.

40:41.340 --> 40:42.421
Good.

40:42.540 --> 40:45.430
Then you can share bananas
with your nigger friend in the stable.

40:45.540 --> 40:47.781
So,

40:47.940 --> 40:50.147
the new sheriff of Red Rock
is traveling with you?

40:50.260 --> 40:51.591
Oh, he's lying.

40:51.700 --> 40:53.623
He ain't sheriff of nothin'.

40:53.740 --> 40:55.663
He's a Southern renegade.

40:55.820 --> 40:59.344
He's just talking hisself
out of freezing to death is all.

40:59.460 --> 41:01.428
What the fuck I tell you about talking, huh?

41:01.540 --> 41:03.065
I'll bust you in the mouth

41:03.180 --> 41:05.421
right in front of these people.
I don't give a fuck!

41:05.580 --> 41:07.105
You never gave your name, sir.

41:07.220 --> 41:09.348
John Ruth.

41:09.500 --> 41:10.581
Are you a lawman?

41:10.700 --> 41:12.065
I'm taking her to the law.

41:12.180 --> 41:13.545
So you're a bounty hunter?

41:13.660 --> 41:15.901
That's right, buster.

41:17.980 --> 41:19.709
Do you have a warrant?

41:19.820 --> 41:21.151
(SCOFFS): Yeah, course I do.

41:21.260 --> 41:22.546
May I see it?

41:25.900 --> 41:27.470
Why?

41:27.580 --> 41:30.663
Ah. You're supposed
to produce it upon request.

41:30.780 --> 41:33.511
How am I supposed to know
you're not a villain,

41:33.620 --> 41:36.021
kidnapping this woman,

41:36.140 --> 41:38.108
without a warrant in your possession?

41:40.180 --> 41:41.864
What's your name, buster?

41:41.980 --> 41:45.905
Well, it certainly isn't Buster.

41:47.180 --> 41:50.502
It's Oswaldo Mobray.

41:51.660 --> 41:53.025
Oswaldo?

41:53.140 --> 41:54.585
Yes.

41:55.780 --> 41:57.703
Well,

41:57.820 --> 42:01.108
I got my warrant, Oswaldo.

42:14.540 --> 42:15.666
I take it you're Daisy Domergue?

42:15.780 --> 42:17.384
- That's her.
- Yeah.

42:19.020 --> 42:20.624
(SOFTLY): I see.

42:22.260 --> 42:25.707
Uh, it says here "dead or alive."

42:25.820 --> 42:27.663
Yeah. It does.

42:27.780 --> 42:29.828
Well, transporting a desperate,

42:29.940 --> 42:32.341
hostile prisoner such as her

42:32.500 --> 42:34.309
sounds like hard work.

42:34.460 --> 42:37.384
Wouldn't transporting her be easier

42:37.500 --> 42:38.945
if she were dead?

42:39.060 --> 42:41.745
Well, no one said the job
was supposed to be easy.

42:41.860 --> 42:44.386
And why is her hanging proper
so important to you?

42:44.500 --> 42:46.309
Let's just say I don't like
cheatin' the hangman.

42:46.420 --> 42:48.104
He got to make a living, too.

42:48.220 --> 42:50.587
Well, I appreciate that.

42:50.700 --> 42:53.590
Allow me to properly

42:53.700 --> 42:55.589
introduce myself.

42:55.700 --> 43:00.141
I'm Oswaldo Mobray,
the hangman in these parts.

43:03.380 --> 43:05.144
(JOHN CHUCKLES)

43:05.260 --> 43:07.149
- La-di-da.
- Ah.

43:07.260 --> 43:08.750
Looks like I brought you a customer.

43:08.860 --> 43:09.986
Yeah, so it would appear.

43:10.100 --> 43:11.864
You ever spent two days or more

43:11.980 --> 43:15.063
locked up with one of your customers before?

43:15.180 --> 43:17.182
- I can't say I have.
- Don't talk to my prisoner.

43:17.300 --> 43:18.745
I talk to my prisoner, that's it.

43:18.860 --> 43:19.941
- You got it?
- I got it.

43:20.060 --> 43:21.266
(CHUCKLES) Jolly good.

43:21.380 --> 43:24.864
You got anything in here besides
coffee that can help warm us up?

43:24.980 --> 43:27.187
Well, the bar is open.

43:27.300 --> 43:29.951
Follow moi. (CHUCKLES)

43:31.620 --> 43:33.588
(WIND WHISTLING)

43:42.420 --> 43:45.424
Line, O.B.!

43:45.540 --> 43:47.190
O.B.: Oh, whoa.

43:47.300 --> 43:48.825
Oh.

43:50.580 --> 43:52.264
Whoa.

43:52.380 --> 43:54.348
(♪♪♪)

44:12.260 --> 44:13.750
BOB: Hey.

44:21.860 --> 44:24.943
(HORSE NEIGHING)

44:25.060 --> 44:27.631
Whoa, Ace, whoa.

44:27.780 --> 44:31.023
You're all right, you're all right.

44:31.140 --> 44:32.904
CHRIS: Come on, goddamn it. I'm cold!

44:33.020 --> 44:34.988
(HORSE NEIGHING)

44:39.340 --> 44:41.468
BOB: I'll feed and water the horses.

44:41.580 --> 44:44.550
You go inside and get some hot coffee.

44:44.660 --> 44:46.150
Got some stew cooking.

44:46.300 --> 44:47.347
Should be done soon.

44:47.460 --> 44:48.700
Now, look.

44:48.820 --> 44:52.222
No matter how bad this blizzard gets,

44:52.340 --> 44:57.186
we still got to feed these horses
and take a squat from time to time.

44:57.300 --> 45:00.383
So me and Chris better lay out a line

45:00.500 --> 45:02.662
from the stable to the front door

45:02.820 --> 45:05.664
and from the front door to the shithouse.

45:05.820 --> 45:07.310
Okay?

45:10.740 --> 45:12.344
Good idea.

45:13.460 --> 45:15.110
Come on, Chris.

45:16.820 --> 45:18.265
I'll give you a hand.

45:19.820 --> 45:22.505
Oh, no, no, no, no, no. Go inside. Get warm.

45:22.620 --> 45:24.463
You're doin' stable work
in a goddamn blizzard.

45:24.580 --> 45:26.309
I offer to help, you say no?

45:27.860 --> 45:29.908
You're right, amigo.

45:30.020 --> 45:31.909
Muchas gracias.

45:34.140 --> 45:35.983
O.B.: All right. Follow me.

45:36.140 --> 45:38.541
(O.B. AND CHRIS GRUNTING)

45:38.660 --> 45:41.027
(GRUNTING CONTINUES)

45:46.900 --> 45:50.586
We're gonna drop one every ten paces,

45:50.740 --> 45:52.310
- from here to the door.
- Yeah!

45:52.420 --> 45:54.229
All right!

45:58.340 --> 46:00.661
(COUGHING)

46:00.780 --> 46:02.748
(♪♪♪)

46:18.180 --> 46:20.547
(♪♪♪)

46:39.420 --> 46:41.866
(♪♪♪)

46:53.900 --> 46:57.461
Now, you're wanted for murder.

46:57.580 --> 47:01.788
For the sake of my analogy,
let's just assume that you did it.

47:01.900 --> 47:04.028
Now, John Ruth wants
to take you back to Red Rock

47:04.140 --> 47:06.063
to stand trial for murder.

47:06.180 --> 47:09.309
And if you're found guilty,

47:09.420 --> 47:13.063
the people of Red Rock
will hang you in the town square.

47:13.180 --> 47:14.989
And, as the hangman,

47:15.100 --> 47:18.309
I will perform the execution.

47:18.420 --> 47:21.026
And if all those things

47:21.140 --> 47:22.983
end up taking place,

47:23.100 --> 47:26.104
that's what civilized society

47:26.220 --> 47:29.542
calls justice.

47:29.660 --> 47:31.549
However,

47:31.660 --> 47:34.823
if the relatives and the loved ones

47:34.940 --> 47:38.390
of the person you murdered
were outside that door right now,

47:38.500 --> 47:40.821
and after busting down that door,

47:40.940 --> 47:43.386
they drug you out into the snow

47:43.500 --> 47:45.548
and hung you up by the neck,

47:45.660 --> 47:49.028
that would be frontier justice.

47:49.140 --> 47:52.064
Now, the good part

47:52.180 --> 47:53.909
about frontier justice

47:54.020 --> 47:57.661
is it's very thirst-quenching.

47:57.780 --> 48:02.229
The bad part is
it's apt to be wrong as right.

48:02.340 --> 48:03.671
Well, not in your case.

48:03.780 --> 48:05.111
In your case, you'd have it coming.

48:05.220 --> 48:08.383
But other people, maybe not so much.

48:08.500 --> 48:12.510
OSWALDO: But ultimately, what's
the real difference between the two?

48:12.620 --> 48:16.261
The real difference is me.

48:16.380 --> 48:17.870
The hangman.

48:17.980 --> 48:19.744
To me, it doesn't matter what you did.

48:19.860 --> 48:22.101
When I hang you, I'll get no
satisfaction from your death.

48:22.220 --> 48:23.301
It's my job.

48:23.420 --> 48:24.865
I hang you in Red Rock.

48:25.020 --> 48:26.704
I move on to the next town.

48:26.820 --> 48:30.666
I hang someone else there.

48:30.780 --> 48:34.910
The man who pulls the lever
that breaks your neck

48:35.020 --> 48:37.910
will be a dispassionate man.

48:38.020 --> 48:42.309
And that dispassion
is the very essence of justice.

48:42.420 --> 48:46.220
For justice delivered without dispassion

48:46.340 --> 48:50.982
is always in danger of not being justice.

48:51.100 --> 48:52.511
JOHN: Amen.

48:58.340 --> 48:59.990
(SNIFFS)

49:17.780 --> 49:19.191
JOHN: No offense, cowboy fella.

49:19.300 --> 49:22.224
Just gettin' your attention.

49:22.340 --> 49:25.742
Yeah, well... (SIGHS)

49:25.860 --> 49:27.783
you got it.

49:27.900 --> 49:30.551
What you writin', friend?

49:30.660 --> 49:32.947
Only thing I'm qualified to write about.

49:33.060 --> 49:35.222
What's that?

49:35.380 --> 49:37.348
My life story.

49:37.460 --> 49:39.144
You're writing your life story?

49:39.300 --> 49:40.665
You bet I am.

49:40.780 --> 49:42.145
Am I in it?

49:42.260 --> 49:44.103
(CHUCKLES)

49:44.220 --> 49:45.824
You just entered.

49:45.940 --> 49:47.226
(CHUCKLES)

49:47.340 --> 49:48.990
Well, you like writing stories so much,

49:49.100 --> 49:51.307
why don't you tell me
the story that brings you here?

49:52.580 --> 49:54.150
Who's asking?

49:54.260 --> 49:56.149
I am. John Ruth.

49:56.260 --> 49:58.661
I'm bringing in this one to Red Rock to hang.

49:58.820 --> 50:00.982
And ain't no way I'm spending
a couple of nights

50:01.100 --> 50:03.387
under a roof with somebody
I don't know who they are,

50:03.500 --> 50:05.025
and I don't know who you are.

50:05.140 --> 50:07.108
So, who are you?

50:07.220 --> 50:09.109
Joe Gage.

50:09.220 --> 50:11.188
- What?
- That's my name.

50:11.300 --> 50:12.506
Joe Gage.

50:12.620 --> 50:14.429
Okay, Joe Gage.

50:14.540 --> 50:16.269
Why you going to Red Rock?

50:16.420 --> 50:18.422
I ain't, I ain't, I ain't going to Red Rock.

50:18.540 --> 50:19.985
Where you going?

50:20.100 --> 50:22.023
About nine miles outside of Red Rock.

50:22.180 --> 50:23.227
What's there?

50:23.340 --> 50:24.671
My mother.

50:25.780 --> 50:27.066
Your mother?

50:27.180 --> 50:29.228
Listen, I'm just a cowpuncher.

50:29.340 --> 50:33.390
I just, uh, got back
from a long drive, and...

50:33.500 --> 50:38.028
and I wasn't just an ass
in a saddle this time.

50:38.140 --> 50:40.507
I was a partner.

50:40.620 --> 50:44.420
First time in my life I made a pretty penny.

50:44.540 --> 50:46.110
And, uh,

50:46.220 --> 50:50.424
figured I'd come home
and spend time with my mother

50:50.580 --> 50:52.264
for Christmas.

50:52.380 --> 50:53.905
Now, that's funny.

50:54.020 --> 50:55.146
(CHUCKLES)

50:55.260 --> 50:58.744
'Cause you don't look like
the coming-home-for-Christmas type.

50:58.860 --> 51:02.421
Yeah, well, (LAUGHS)

51:02.540 --> 51:05.623
you know, looks can be deceiving.

51:07.660 --> 51:10.630
Because I definitely am a

51:10.740 --> 51:14.631
coming-home-for-Christmas-
to-spend-time-with-Mother type.

51:15.940 --> 51:20.070
Christmas with Mother, I mean, uh,

51:20.180 --> 51:22.182
it's a wonderful thing.

51:23.740 --> 51:26.107
Now, is that, uh,

51:26.220 --> 51:27.904
good enough for you,

51:28.020 --> 51:30.307
John Ruth?

51:31.580 --> 51:33.582
For now.

51:33.700 --> 51:36.226
You steer clear of my prisoner.

51:40.620 --> 51:42.748
Hello, old-timer.

51:44.700 --> 51:46.304
General.

51:47.540 --> 51:48.951
General.

51:50.460 --> 51:53.782
You, sir, are a hyena.

51:55.620 --> 51:57.941
I have no wish to speak to you.

52:02.540 --> 52:04.668
I've been called worse.

52:06.780 --> 52:08.942
(SIGHS) Fair enough, General.

52:10.220 --> 52:11.870
Sorry to bother you.

52:13.900 --> 52:15.470
- (POUNDING)
- CHRIS and O.B.: Hey!

52:15.580 --> 52:17.309
- You gotta kick it open!
- Gotta kick it open!

52:17.460 --> 52:19.144
- CHRIS and O.B.: What?
- Kick it open!

52:19.260 --> 52:21.342
- That latch, you gotta kick it open!
- You gotta kick it open!

52:22.420 --> 52:23.626
CHRIS: Jesus Christ!

52:23.740 --> 52:25.105
- JOHN: Close it!
- DOMERGUE: Close it!

52:25.260 --> 52:26.546
- JOHN: Close the door!
- CHRIS: What?

52:26.660 --> 52:28.105
- DOMERGUE: Close it!
- JOE: The goddamn door!

52:28.260 --> 52:30.945
- JOHN: It doesn't have a latch. Close it!
- JOE: It's already cold enough in here!

52:32.260 --> 52:34.866
(GROANING)

52:35.020 --> 52:36.704
JOHN: Doesn't have a latch.

52:36.820 --> 52:38.629
- You gotta hammer up a board.
- JOE: You gotta nail it shut!

52:38.740 --> 52:40.026
The hammer and nails by the door.

52:40.140 --> 52:42.620
There's a hammer and nails right there!

52:42.740 --> 52:44.902
Ah, God!

52:45.020 --> 52:47.341
- Hold this here, Chris.
- Here! Here.

52:55.140 --> 52:56.585
- O.B.: Watch your fingers.
- CHRIS: Yeah.

52:56.700 --> 52:58.464
- Really nail it in!
- O.B.: Yeah.

53:01.060 --> 53:02.789
JOHN: You need two pieces of wood.

53:02.900 --> 53:04.664
You got to hammer another one.

53:04.780 --> 53:06.544
JOE: One ain't good enough!

53:06.660 --> 53:08.583
It's gonna blow right open!

53:08.700 --> 53:09.781
Now, goddamn it!

53:09.900 --> 53:11.664
Gonna open if you don't ham...!

53:11.780 --> 53:13.350
- Shut up!
- CHRIS: Ah, got it!

53:13.460 --> 53:15.747
- O.B.: Son of a bitch!
- (CHRIS GROANS)

53:25.980 --> 53:27.425
(PANTING)

53:27.540 --> 53:28.905
Jesus Christ.

53:29.020 --> 53:30.909
That's door's a whore.

53:31.020 --> 53:33.500
(TOSSES HAMMER ON FLOOR)

53:33.660 --> 53:34.991
Oh.

53:35.100 --> 53:36.750
I get it. "Haberdashery."

53:36.860 --> 53:38.703
That was a joke.

53:38.820 --> 53:41.107
- How's the coffee?
- (COFFEE POURING)

53:41.220 --> 53:44.781
JOHN: Now? Pretty good,
if I do say so myself.

53:47.340 --> 53:48.865
Thank you.

53:48.980 --> 53:51.108
(SIGHS, PANTS)

53:51.260 --> 53:53.945
Ooh!

53:55.140 --> 53:56.710
(CHRIS SIGHS)

53:56.820 --> 53:59.300
(CHRIS PANTING, SHIVERING)

54:03.420 --> 54:05.741
Ha! Navajo!

54:05.900 --> 54:07.629
Guess who he is.

54:09.540 --> 54:11.827
Buffalo Bill?

54:11.940 --> 54:13.544
(LAUGHS) Hardly.

54:13.700 --> 54:15.384
No. I'm...

54:15.500 --> 54:17.229
Oswaldo Mobray. I'm the...

54:17.340 --> 54:19.388
He's the hangman of Red Rock.

54:20.500 --> 54:21.661
Oh, you are?

54:21.780 --> 54:23.828
- Yes, I am.
- (LAUGHS): Well!

54:23.940 --> 54:26.511
- Uh, good to meet you, uh,
- Yeah.

54:26.620 --> 54:28.065
- Mr....?
- Uh, Mobray.

54:28.180 --> 54:29.261
- Mobray.
- Yeah.

54:29.380 --> 54:30.427
I'm Chris Mannix.

54:30.540 --> 54:31.951
The new sheriff in Red Rock.

54:32.060 --> 54:34.301
- Really?
- Pfft, horseshit!

54:34.420 --> 54:35.865
Pay no attention to him.

54:35.980 --> 54:37.470
Horseshit!

54:37.580 --> 54:39.264
Fella warmin' himself by that potbelly stove

54:39.380 --> 54:41.860
- is a hell of a driver named O.B.
- Ah.

54:42.020 --> 54:44.421
That's the only thing
you've said that's the truth.

54:46.020 --> 54:48.102
You comin' into Red Rock
to hang Lance Lawson?

54:48.220 --> 54:50.268
- Precisely.
- Do you have the execution orders on you?

54:50.380 --> 54:51.984
- In my bag.
- May I see 'em?

54:52.100 --> 54:53.704
Of course. (CHUCKLES)

54:53.820 --> 54:55.026
(CHRIS SIGHS)

54:58.820 --> 55:01.027
Who's, uh, who's Lance Lawson?

55:01.140 --> 55:05.150
He's a fella been sittin'
in the Red Rock jail about a month now.

55:05.260 --> 55:07.342
He's the fella who shot the fella

55:07.460 --> 55:09.986
who was sheriff 'fore me.

55:10.100 --> 55:12.387
- Precisely.
- (WIND WHISTLING)

55:12.500 --> 55:13.945
(CHRIS MUMBLING)

55:14.060 --> 55:16.188
Thank you.

55:16.300 --> 55:19.383
(CHRIS SHIVERS, EXHALES)

55:21.460 --> 55:24.066
What did she mean when she said,

55:24.180 --> 55:27.024
"The bounty hunter's
nigger friend in the stable"?

55:27.140 --> 55:30.383
He's got a nigger bounty hunter
friend in the stable.

55:30.500 --> 55:32.628
But all that just to guard her?

55:32.780 --> 55:35.909
Uh, I don't think that was
the original idea, but...

55:36.020 --> 55:38.626
- that's the idea now.
- Oh. Mm.

55:38.740 --> 55:41.027
Want a little snake bite in your coffee?

55:41.140 --> 55:42.904
- DOMERGUE: Yeah.
- (CHUCKLES)

55:43.020 --> 55:44.545
OSWALDO: Five of you?

55:44.660 --> 55:46.662
Well, well, well, looks
like Minnie's Haberdashery

55:46.780 --> 55:49.181
is about to get cozy for the next few days.

55:49.340 --> 55:50.830
Yes, it does.

55:54.500 --> 55:55.911
- Here.
- Ah. Ah.

55:56.020 --> 55:58.466
(WIND HOWLING)

55:58.580 --> 55:59.820
(CHRIS EXHALES)

55:59.940 --> 56:03.183
Are you the chap with the Lincoln letter?

56:03.300 --> 56:05.109
The Lincoln what?

56:05.220 --> 56:08.702
Yes. The letter from Abraham Lincoln.

56:08.860 --> 56:10.862
President Abraham Lincoln?

56:10.980 --> 56:13.745
Yes. Weren't you pen pals?

56:13.860 --> 56:16.067
With the president?

56:16.180 --> 56:19.184
Well, I'm sorry, I heard
that somebody in your party

56:19.300 --> 56:21.064
had a letter from Abraham Lincoln.

56:21.180 --> 56:22.670
I assumed it was you.

56:22.780 --> 56:24.066
Not him!

56:24.180 --> 56:26.865
Black fella in the stable.

56:26.980 --> 56:28.470
The nigger...

56:28.580 --> 56:31.868
in the stable has a letter
from Abraham Lincoln?

56:31.980 --> 56:33.630
Yeah.

56:33.740 --> 56:38.462
The nigger in the stable has
a letter from Abraham Lincoln?

56:38.580 --> 56:40.070
(WIND WHISTLING)

56:40.220 --> 56:43.190
(CHICKENS CLUCKING, HORSE NEIGHING)

56:53.500 --> 56:55.787
What'd you say your name was again?

56:55.900 --> 56:57.789
- Bob.
- Warren.

56:57.900 --> 57:00.141
Minnie and Sweet Dave in there?

57:00.260 --> 57:02.388
Minnie and Sweet Dave went
to visit her mother

57:02.500 --> 57:04.264
on the north side of the mountain.

57:04.380 --> 57:05.825
- What?
- Yeah.

57:05.940 --> 57:07.271
Minnie ain't here?

57:07.380 --> 57:09.906
Yes, they're visiting her mother.

57:10.020 --> 57:12.102
- Her mother?
- Yes.

57:12.220 --> 57:13.665
Hmm.

57:15.260 --> 57:17.547
Never knew Minnie had a mother.

57:19.740 --> 57:22.630
Well, everybody's got a mother.

57:24.140 --> 57:26.063
Yeah, I suppose.

57:26.180 --> 57:28.786
(HORSE GRUNTS, HUFFS)

57:28.940 --> 57:31.102
And she left you in charge?

57:31.220 --> 57:32.585
Si.

57:32.700 --> 57:34.589
(WARREN CHUCKLES)

57:34.700 --> 57:37.783
That sure don't sound like Minnie.

57:37.900 --> 57:40.141
Are you calling me a liar?

57:40.260 --> 57:41.989
(HORSE HUFFS)

57:42.100 --> 57:44.580
Well, not yet I ain't.

57:44.700 --> 57:46.941
Just sounds peculiar is all.

57:47.060 --> 57:48.949
What sounds peculiar?

57:49.060 --> 57:53.029
Well, first off, Minnie never struck me
as the sentimental type.

57:53.140 --> 57:56.940
And secondly, I can't imagine
Sweet Dave lifting his fat ass

57:57.060 --> 57:58.789
out his chair long enough to fetch well water

57:58.900 --> 58:01.187
unless Minnie was laying
a frying pan upside his head,

58:01.300 --> 58:03.302
let alone take a trip to the north side.

58:03.420 --> 58:05.661
Well, that sounds a whole lot

58:05.780 --> 58:08.386
like you're calling me a liar,
mi negro amigo.

58:08.500 --> 58:10.150
(CHUCKLES)

58:10.260 --> 58:12.149
Yeah, it do sound a whole lot
like that, don't it?

58:13.700 --> 58:16.385
But I still ain't done it yet.

58:17.460 --> 58:20.464
Minnie still serve food?

58:20.580 --> 58:23.311
- Do you consider stew food?
- Yes.

58:23.420 --> 58:25.070
Then we serve food.

58:25.180 --> 58:28.787
She still stinking up the place
with Old Quail pipe tobacco?

58:30.940 --> 58:32.669
(BOB CHUCKLES)

58:32.780 --> 58:35.545
Minnie doesn't smoke a pipe.

58:35.660 --> 58:37.742
She rolls her own.

58:37.860 --> 58:40.431
Red Apple Tobacco.

58:40.540 --> 58:44.545
But, mi negro amigo,
I think you already know this.

58:44.660 --> 58:46.822
Yeah, I do, Senor Bob.

58:46.940 --> 58:49.511
Just seeing if you do.

58:49.620 --> 58:51.987
(WIND WHIPPING)

59:00.780 --> 59:02.908
(BOB GRUNTING)

59:04.140 --> 59:06.188
(WIND WHISTLING, RUSHING)

59:06.300 --> 59:07.825
BOB (FAINTLY): Come on!

59:07.940 --> 59:09.863
(CONTINUES INDISTINCTLY)

59:16.700 --> 59:19.021
(WIND WHIPPING, WHISTLING)

59:32.100 --> 59:33.386
Fill 'er up, O.B.

59:33.500 --> 59:35.343
Yeah.

59:35.460 --> 59:37.428
JOHN: Goddamn it.

59:39.220 --> 59:40.631
Thank you.

59:40.780 --> 59:41.986
(EXHALES)

59:43.060 --> 59:44.869
(SLURPING)

59:44.980 --> 59:46.391
(EXHALES)

59:48.500 --> 59:51.947
CHRIS: Well, cut my legs off
and call me Shorty.

59:52.060 --> 59:55.348
Is that General Sanford Smithers I see?

59:57.020 --> 59:59.068
You got a good eye, son.

59:59.180 --> 01:00:03.344
Ha-ha! Well, I'll be double-dog damned!

01:00:03.460 --> 01:00:05.462
General Sandy "Don't Give a Damn" Smithers?

01:00:05.580 --> 01:00:07.184
(CHRIS CLEARS THROAT)

01:00:08.700 --> 01:00:10.941
Captain Chris Mannix, Mannix's Marauders.

01:00:11.100 --> 01:00:12.590
Erskine's boy?

01:00:12.700 --> 01:00:14.384
Yes, sir.

01:00:14.500 --> 01:00:17.583
Uh... may I sit down, sir?

01:00:17.700 --> 01:00:20.431
Well, according to the Yankees,
it's a free country.

01:00:20.540 --> 01:00:23.783
General Sandy Smithers. Ha-ha!

01:00:23.900 --> 01:00:26.107
Boy...

01:00:26.220 --> 01:00:27.745
oh, boy,

01:00:27.860 --> 01:00:31.148
did my daddy talk about you!

01:00:31.260 --> 01:00:34.946
I heard you gave
those Blue Bellies sweet hell.

01:00:35.060 --> 01:00:36.630
(SMITHERS CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

01:00:36.740 --> 01:00:38.822
Me and my boys did our part.

01:00:38.940 --> 01:00:41.341
Just like Erskine and his boys
did their part.

01:00:41.460 --> 01:00:43.224
Hell yeah, we did.

01:00:43.380 --> 01:00:45.428
Yankee sons of bitches.

01:00:45.540 --> 01:00:48.862
I never knew your father, son.

01:00:48.980 --> 01:00:53.463
But I always respected his resolve.

01:00:53.580 --> 01:00:55.628
Well, thank you for saying that, General.

01:00:55.740 --> 01:00:58.471
Your respect would have meant
the world to him.

01:01:00.140 --> 01:01:02.905
Can I get you some coffee?

01:01:03.020 --> 01:01:04.624
That'd be nice.

01:01:04.780 --> 01:01:06.828
Well, how about a blanket?

01:01:06.940 --> 01:01:08.226
(SMITHERS CHUCKLES)

01:01:08.340 --> 01:01:10.263
That'd be even nicer.

01:01:10.380 --> 01:01:13.111
Hell, you know what? You can have mine.

01:01:14.780 --> 01:01:16.350
(EXHALES)

01:01:16.500 --> 01:01:18.502
Here we go, General.

01:01:20.100 --> 01:01:23.183
Ha-ha! So what brings you
out Wyoming way, sir?

01:01:23.340 --> 01:01:25.149
If you don't mind my askin'.

01:01:25.300 --> 01:01:27.064
My boy.

01:01:27.220 --> 01:01:30.781
- Oh, you got a boy that lives in Red Rock?
- My son.

01:01:31.860 --> 01:01:34.340
Chester Charles Smithers.

01:01:34.460 --> 01:01:37.828
He died out here a few years back.

01:01:37.980 --> 01:01:40.062
Oh, forgive me, sir.

01:01:40.180 --> 01:01:42.467
There's no forgiveness needed, son.

01:01:43.820 --> 01:01:46.983
Like I said, it was a few years back.

01:01:47.100 --> 01:01:49.785
It was after he'd served his service.

01:01:49.900 --> 01:01:51.709
(WIND HOWLING)

01:01:51.820 --> 01:01:56.109
He came out here to the hills of Wyoming...

01:01:56.220 --> 01:01:58.029
to make his fortune.

01:01:59.500 --> 01:02:02.868
(QUIETLY): Never to be heard from again.

01:02:04.860 --> 01:02:08.182
(WIND WHISTLING, HOWLING)

01:02:08.340 --> 01:02:12.390
I bought him a symbolic plot...

01:02:12.500 --> 01:02:15.743
in the Red Rock cemetery.

01:02:15.860 --> 01:02:20.229
And I'm here to advise
a stone maker on his headstone.

01:02:20.340 --> 01:02:22.741
Was he a goner for sure?

01:02:22.900 --> 01:02:26.425
No chance he could be livin'
the cold life out in the woods?

01:02:26.540 --> 01:02:29.350
It's a rough life, but folks can learn it.

01:02:29.460 --> 01:02:32.907
If he'd have done
what he came out here to do,

01:02:33.020 --> 01:02:35.307
he'd have come home.

01:02:35.420 --> 01:02:36.945
- (WIND HOWLING, WHISTLING)
- (BOB GRUNTING)

01:02:37.060 --> 01:02:39.506
BOB: Hold it. Close it, close it!

01:02:39.620 --> 01:02:41.110
(GRUNTS)

01:02:42.740 --> 01:02:45.550
You have to hold it closed
while I nail it shut.

01:02:45.660 --> 01:02:47.867
WARREN: Well, who's the idiot
broke the damn door?

01:02:47.980 --> 01:02:49.470
(STAMMERING): Oh, j...

01:02:49.580 --> 01:02:51.901
just fucking hold it closed!

01:02:53.180 --> 01:02:55.308
Orale, cabron!

01:02:55.420 --> 01:02:57.468
(WIND WHISTLING)

01:02:57.580 --> 01:02:59.947
Hold it closed.

01:03:00.100 --> 01:03:01.625
Okay.

01:03:01.740 --> 01:03:03.344
One more.

01:03:04.420 --> 01:03:06.263
(WIND HOWLING)

01:03:06.380 --> 01:03:09.145
BOB: Keep holding, keep holding,

01:03:09.260 --> 01:03:11.149
- my negro amigo.
- (HAMMERING CONTINUES)

01:03:11.260 --> 01:03:13.262
(BOB MUMBLING)

01:03:13.380 --> 01:03:16.270
BOB: We need two pieces of wood.

01:03:16.380 --> 01:03:18.906
(BOB GRUNTING)

01:03:19.020 --> 01:03:21.261
Orale, cabron! All right.

01:03:21.380 --> 01:03:23.860
There you go, motherfucker!

01:03:23.980 --> 01:03:26.381
- (BOB SIGHS)
- (DROPS HAMMER)

01:03:27.580 --> 01:03:29.787
Lot of hats, Senor Bob.

01:03:29.900 --> 01:03:31.425
Huh?

01:03:31.540 --> 01:03:33.508
Considering Minnie's
"no hats indoors" policy,

01:03:33.620 --> 01:03:37.583
which, if I remember correctly,
was one of them Bar of Iron rules.

01:03:37.700 --> 01:03:40.306
Kind of rule she'd want kept up
in her absence.

01:03:40.420 --> 01:03:42.309
You seem to have a laissez-faire attitude

01:03:42.420 --> 01:03:44.309
when it come to the hats.

01:03:44.420 --> 01:03:45.785
I'm guilty.

01:03:45.940 --> 01:03:48.591
I have a laissez-faire attitude
about the hats.

01:03:48.700 --> 01:03:51.146
How about we forget about the hats today

01:03:51.260 --> 01:03:54.070
considering there is
a blizzard going on and on?

01:03:54.180 --> 01:03:56.547
We'll make tomorrow "No Hat Day"!

01:03:56.700 --> 01:03:58.987
(WIND WHISTLING, HOWLING)

