I know Americans aren't apt

01:06:41.180 --> 01:06:44.024
to let a little thing
like unconditional surrender

01:06:44.140 --> 01:06:46.791
get in the way of a good war.

01:06:46.900 --> 01:06:49.665
But I strongly suggest we don't restage

01:06:49.780 --> 01:06:52.101
the Battle of Baton Rouge

01:06:52.220 --> 01:06:54.791
during a blizzard in Minnie's Haberdashery.

01:06:54.900 --> 01:06:56.345
(WIND CONTINUES WHISTLING)

01:06:56.460 --> 01:06:58.110
Now, uh...

01:06:58.220 --> 01:07:00.348
my Nubian friend...

01:07:00.460 --> 01:07:03.225
while I realize passions are high,

01:07:03.340 --> 01:07:05.308
that was a while ago.

01:07:05.420 --> 01:07:08.742
And if you shoot this unarmed old man,

01:07:08.860 --> 01:07:11.830
I guarantee I will hang you by the neck

01:07:11.980 --> 01:07:15.666
until you are dead
once we arrive in Red Rock.

01:07:19.620 --> 01:07:21.827
I damn well guarantee that, too.

01:07:21.940 --> 01:07:25.070
JOHN: Yeah, Warren,
that's the problem with old men.

01:07:25.180 --> 01:07:27.023
You can kick 'em down the stairs

01:07:27.140 --> 01:07:30.542
and say it's a accident,
but you can't just shoot 'em.

01:07:30.660 --> 01:07:33.391
OSWALDO: Uh, gentlemen... since we may be

01:07:33.540 --> 01:07:35.542
(SMACKS LIPS) trapped here,

01:07:35.660 --> 01:07:37.549
close together-like,

01:07:37.660 --> 01:07:39.867
for a few days,

01:07:39.980 --> 01:07:43.382
may I suggest a possible solution?

01:07:44.660 --> 01:07:47.584
We divide Minnie's in half.

01:07:47.700 --> 01:07:49.748
The Northern side

01:07:49.860 --> 01:07:52.386
and the Southern side.

01:07:52.500 --> 01:07:55.265
With the dinner table...

01:07:55.380 --> 01:07:57.667
operating as a...

01:07:57.780 --> 01:07:59.669
neutral territory.

01:07:59.820 --> 01:08:02.790
We could say that the fireplace...

01:08:02.900 --> 01:08:05.267
side of the room acts as a...

01:08:05.380 --> 01:08:09.180
a symbolic representative of...

01:08:09.300 --> 01:08:10.825
Georgia.

01:08:12.700 --> 01:08:14.987
While the bar...

01:08:15.100 --> 01:08:16.750
represents...

01:08:20.540 --> 01:08:22.702
Philadelphia!

01:08:22.819 --> 01:08:25.823
Long as the bar's Philadelphia...

01:08:25.939 --> 01:08:27.863
I agree.

01:08:35.220 --> 01:08:38.109
We still got that deal
we talked about in the wagon?

01:08:38.220 --> 01:08:41.269
- O.B.: Thank you.
- I help you protect your $8,000,

01:08:41.380 --> 01:08:44.782
- you help me protect my ten?
- Yeah, I suppose.

01:08:45.859 --> 01:08:47.669
One of them fellas

01:08:47.779 --> 01:08:51.261
is not what he says he is.

01:08:51.380 --> 01:08:52.904
O.B.: What is he?

01:08:53.020 --> 01:08:56.024
In cahoots with this one, that's what he is.

01:08:56.140 --> 01:08:58.746
One of them, maybe even two of them,

01:08:58.859 --> 01:09:01.988
is here to see Domergue goes free.

01:09:02.100 --> 01:09:06.662
To accomplish that goal,
they'll kill everybody in here.

01:09:06.779 --> 01:09:11.027
They got 'em a couple of days,
so all they got to do is sit tight

01:09:11.180 --> 01:09:14.548
and wait for a window of opportunity.

01:09:14.660 --> 01:09:17.231
And that's when they strike.

01:09:18.939 --> 01:09:21.546
Huh, bitch?

01:09:21.660 --> 01:09:24.185
If you say so, John.

01:09:24.300 --> 01:09:25.904
(WIND CONTINUES WHISTLING)

01:09:26.020 --> 01:09:28.341
Are you sure you ain't just being paranoid?

01:09:28.460 --> 01:09:31.350
Our best bet is this duplicitous fella

01:09:31.460 --> 01:09:34.384
