01:09:34.540 --> 01:09:37.145
He won't have the leather patience it takes

01:09:37.260 --> 01:09:39.991
to just sit here and... wait.

01:09:40.100 --> 01:09:42.307
- (STRIKES PIANO KEYS)
- Waiting for an opportunity

01:09:42.460 --> 01:09:45.669
and knowing it's the right one isn't so easy.

01:09:45.779 --> 01:09:49.582
He can't handle it, he'll stop waitin'.

01:09:49.700 --> 01:09:51.667
Try and create his opportunity,

01:09:51.779 --> 01:09:54.989
and that's when Mr. Jumpy reveals himself.

01:09:55.140 --> 01:09:58.030
WARREN: Now, what you got
to say about all this?

01:09:58.140 --> 01:09:59.710
What do I got to say?

01:09:59.820 --> 01:10:02.710
About John Ruth's ravings?

01:10:02.860 --> 01:10:06.069
(WHISPERS): He's absolutely right.

01:10:06.180 --> 01:10:10.390
(NORMAL VOICE):
Me and one of them fellas is in cahoots.

01:10:10.500 --> 01:10:13.709
We're just waiting
for everybody to go to sleep.

01:10:13.820 --> 01:10:16.346
(WHISPERS): That's when
we're gonna kill y'all.

01:10:18.660 --> 01:10:21.425
JOHN: Okay, everybody.

01:10:23.860 --> 01:10:26.545
JOHN: Hear this.

01:10:28.380 --> 01:10:30.428
This here is Daisy Domergue.

01:10:31.900 --> 01:10:34.790
She's wanted dead or alive for murder.

01:10:34.900 --> 01:10:37.471
$10,000. (SNIFFS)

01:10:37.580 --> 01:10:40.231
That money's mine, boys.

01:10:40.340 --> 01:10:42.991
Don't want to share it,

01:10:43.100 --> 01:10:45.387
and I ain't gonna lose it.

01:10:46.460 --> 01:10:48.349
When that sun comes out,

01:10:48.460 --> 01:10:52.351
I'm taking this woman into Red Rock to hang.

01:10:55.540 --> 01:10:58.271
(WIND WHISTLING)

01:10:58.380 --> 01:10:59.905
Now...

01:11:03.260 --> 01:11:05.991
is there anybody here

01:11:06.100 --> 01:11:09.149
committed to stoppin' me...

01:11:09.300 --> 01:11:11.029
from doing that?

01:11:19.940 --> 01:11:21.385
(WIND HOWLING)

01:11:21.500 --> 01:11:23.309
JOHN: Really?

01:11:23.420 --> 01:11:25.991
Nobody got a problem with this?

01:11:27.500 --> 01:11:29.025
(LOGS CRACKLING IN FIREPLACE)

01:11:29.140 --> 01:11:30.551
(BEDSPRINGS CREAKING)

01:11:31.620 --> 01:11:33.065
Well...

01:11:33.180 --> 01:11:36.150
I guess that's very fortunate for me.

01:11:37.460 --> 01:11:38.950
However...

01:11:39.060 --> 01:11:42.348
I hope you all understand

01:11:42.500 --> 01:11:44.628
I can't just...

01:11:44.740 --> 01:11:46.663
take your word.

01:11:46.780 --> 01:11:49.431
Circumstances force me to...

01:11:49.540 --> 01:11:51.588
take...

01:11:51.700 --> 01:11:53.862
precautions.

01:11:53.980 --> 01:11:56.790
When you say...

01:11:56.900 --> 01:11:59.631
"precautions"...

01:11:59.740 --> 01:12:03.301
why do I feel that you mean me?

01:12:03.420 --> 01:12:05.229
Because I'm gonna take your gun, son.

01:12:05.340 --> 01:12:06.910
You are?

01:12:07.020 --> 01:12:08.465
Yes, I am.

01:12:08.580 --> 01:12:11.823
- Nothing personal.
- Just mine?

01:12:11.940 --> 01:12:14.591
Hangman's got himself a gun, too.

01:12:14.740 --> 01:12:18.381
I'll be dealing with his gun
after I deal with yours.

01:12:18.500 --> 01:12:20.901
- (WIND HOWLING)
- (CLEARS THROAT SOFTLY)

01:12:25.700 --> 01:12:27.623
I feel kind of...

01:12:27.740 --> 01:12:29.629
naked without it.

01:12:29.740 --> 01:12:32.550
JOHN: Oh, I still got mine.

01:12:34.460 --> 01:12:36.542
I'll protect you.

01:12:37.620 --> 01:12:39.782
(LAUGHING)

01:12:42.860 --> 01:12:44.828
(PANTING SOFTLY)

01:12:44.980 --> 01:12:47.221
A bastard's work is never done.

01:12:47.340 --> 01:12:49.422
Huh, John Ruth?

01:12:49.540 --> 01:12:52.544
That's right, Joe Gage.

01:12:52.660 --> 01:12:54.947
- Now, give me the gun.
- If you want it...

01:12:56.540 --> 01:12:58.508
you're gonna have to come and take...

01:12:59.980 --> 01:13:01.869
Calm down.

01:13:01.980 --> 01:13:03.550
(JOE GRUNTS)

01:13:03.660 --> 01:13:06.630
Take your hand away from your gun.

01:13:10.020 --> 01:13:11.988
Blink if you're calm.

01:13:13.100 --> 01:13:14.465
He blink?

01:13:14.580 --> 01:13:15.911
He blinked.

01:13:16.020 --> 01:13:19.229
Blink if you're gonna remain calm.

01:13:22.900 --> 01:13:24.584
He blinked.

01:13:24.700 --> 01:13:26.509
Take his pistol.

01:13:26.620 --> 01:13:27.860
(CLUCKS TONGUE)

01:13:28.020 --> 01:13:30.102
I'm real sorry about this, son.

01:13:32.020 --> 01:13:33.943
(SIGHS): Like I said...

01:13:34.060 --> 01:13:36.381
nothing personal, just...

01:13:36.500 --> 01:13:38.707
a precaution.

01:13:40.420 --> 01:13:42.502
- (BLADE RINGS)
- (EXHALES)

01:13:42.660 --> 01:13:44.708
(WIND CONTINUES WHISTLING)

01:13:58.060 --> 01:13:59.903
(WIND HOWLING)

01:14:17.460 --> 01:14:20.782
(GROANING)

01:14:23.740 --> 01:14:25.822
Pretty sneaky.

01:14:33.820 --> 01:14:36.141
(WIND CONTINUES WHISTLING)

01:14:51.980 --> 01:14:53.903
(CHAIN CLINKING)

01:15:00.580 --> 01:15:03.151
Afraid the same applies to you, too,

01:15:03.260 --> 01:15:05.706
Mr.... Mobray.

01:15:05.820 --> 01:15:07.788
Ah, precautions must be taken

01:15:07.900 --> 01:15:11.188
because life is too sweet to lose.

01:15:15.500 --> 01:15:17.901
Hand me that little bucket.

01:15:28.300 --> 01:15:31.031
O.B.

01:15:31.140 --> 01:15:33.507
Go to the outhouse.

01:15:33.620 --> 01:15:37.261
Take this bucket and...
dump it down the shithole.

01:15:39.340 --> 01:15:41.741
Why do I got to go outside?

01:15:41.860 --> 01:15:43.510
Well, your jacket's already on,

01:15:43.620 --> 01:15:46.624
and I sorta kinda trust you.

01:15:46.740 --> 01:15:49.391
(WIND WHIPPING, RUSHING)

01:15:56.860 --> 01:16:00.103
(WIND CONTINUES RUSHING)

01:16:18.300 --> 01:16:21.144
- JOHN: Grab the other cup.
- DOMERGUE: Yeah, I got it.

01:16:25.300 --> 01:16:27.382
After you, Major.

01:16:36.100 --> 01:16:38.262
(CHAIN RATTLING)

01:16:41.780 --> 01:16:43.908
(CLEARS THROAT)

01:16:44.020 --> 01:16:45.670
Okay.

01:16:47.580 --> 01:16:50.663
I'm gonna cut you loose while we eat.

01:16:50.780 --> 01:16:54.182
Don't get any ideas.
I ain't goin' soft on ya.

01:16:54.300 --> 01:16:57.110
Lift your ass even one inch off that seat,

01:16:57.220 --> 01:17:00.861
and I'll put a bullet
right in your goddamn throat.

01:17:00.980 --> 01:17:03.221
(SMACKS LIPS) Come here.

01:17:07.860 --> 01:17:09.544
(EXHALES)

01:17:18.740 --> 01:17:20.469
(CHRIS SIGHS)

01:17:20.580 --> 01:17:22.184
Oh. (CHUCKLES)

01:17:25.260 --> 01:17:27.661
So, Domergue...

01:17:27.780 --> 01:17:30.909
I suppose this blizzard
counts as a stroke of luck

01:17:31.020 --> 01:17:33.022
far as you're concerned.

01:17:33.180 --> 01:17:35.148
You don't hear me complainin', do ya?

01:17:35.260 --> 01:17:37.388
No, I sure don't.

01:17:38.980 --> 01:17:41.142
(WIND CONTINUES WHISTLING)

01:17:45.140 --> 01:17:47.825
Well, how 'bout you, Oswaldo?

01:17:49.340 --> 01:17:51.149
How 'bout me what?

01:17:51.260 --> 01:17:52.671
Look...

01:17:52.780 --> 01:17:54.862
considering all the things I done for money,

01:17:54.980 --> 01:17:56.869
I ain't one to judge, but...

01:17:56.980 --> 01:17:59.221
don't you feel just the least little bad

01:17:59.340 --> 01:18:01.741
about hangin' a woman?

01:18:01.860 --> 01:18:04.670
Well, until they invent
a trigger a woman can't pull,

01:18:04.780 --> 01:18:07.989
if you're a hangman,
you're going to hang women.

01:18:08.100 --> 01:18:11.862
Well, hell, Ozzie, I guess I ain't
never looked at it like that before.

01:18:11.980 --> 01:18:14.426
When it comes to some of them
mean bastards out there,

01:18:14.540 --> 01:18:16.383
it's the only thing does the job.

01:18:16.500 --> 01:18:19.390
You really only need to hang mean bastards.

01:18:19.500 --> 01:18:22.470
But mean bastards, you need to hang.

01:18:22.580 --> 01:18:25.311
(BANGING ON DOOR)

01:18:25.420 --> 01:18:28.185
(WIND HOWLING)

01:18:29.740 --> 01:18:30.946
(GROANS)

01:18:31.060 --> 01:18:33.711
O.B.: You goddamn son of a bitch!

01:18:34.940 --> 01:18:37.022
I almost died out there!

01:18:37.140 --> 01:18:40.110
(PANTING, GROANING)

01:18:40.220 --> 01:18:43.941
I ain't ever... going out in that shit

01:18:44.060 --> 01:18:47.189
ever, ever again!

01:18:47.340 --> 01:18:50.310
- (HAMMERING)
- (O.B. PANTING, SHIVERING)

01:18:51.940 --> 01:18:53.908
(GRUNTING)

01:18:56.700 --> 01:18:58.429
(GROANS)

01:18:58.540 --> 01:19:01.225
- (PANTING)
- (HAMMERING CONTINUES)

01:19:01.340 --> 01:19:05.140
(LOUD, GASPING BREATHS)

01:19:07.340 --> 01:19:08.944
(O.B. SHIVERING)

01:19:09.060 --> 01:19:10.983
You okay, O.B.?

01:19:11.100 --> 01:19:12.511
I'm fine.

01:19:12.620 --> 01:19:14.429
I'll be fine.

01:19:14.540 --> 01:19:17.589
I just need to get warm. (PANTING)

01:19:21.860 --> 01:19:24.101
You want some stew, O.B.?

01:19:24.220 --> 01:19:25.745
Stew?

01:19:25.860 --> 01:19:28.340
(PANTING): Later.

01:19:28.460 --> 01:19:30.747
(O.B. CONTINUES PANTING)

01:19:30.860 --> 01:19:32.862
O.B.: Oh, yeah.

01:19:32.980 --> 01:19:34.948
O.B.: That's nice. (SIGHS)

01:19:41.660 --> 01:19:44.027
(WIND WHISTLING)

01:19:58.780 --> 01:20:00.464
So...

01:20:00.620 --> 01:20:02.588
how you doing, Black Major?

01:20:02.700 --> 01:20:04.668
I ain't in the mood, Chris Mannix.

01:20:04.780 --> 01:20:07.021
Leave me be from your horseshit.

01:20:08.580 --> 01:20:10.582
John Ruth says you got a Lincoln letter.

01:20:10.700 --> 01:20:13.624
I told you, jackass,
go hee-haw someplace else.

01:20:13.740 --> 01:20:15.344
That's right, John.

01:20:15.460 --> 01:20:17.383
You did say that, didn't you?

01:20:17.500 --> 01:20:19.502
Yeah. I did.

01:20:20.700 --> 01:20:23.431
So...

01:20:23.540 --> 01:20:26.146
you got a letter from Abraham Lincoln?

01:20:26.260 --> 01:20:27.785
Yes.

01:20:27.940 --> 01:20:30.625
The... Abraham Lincoln?

01:20:30.740 --> 01:20:31.980
Yes.

01:20:32.100 --> 01:20:33.465
Abraham Lincoln?

01:20:33.580 --> 01:20:35.389
The president of the United States?

01:20:35.500 --> 01:20:37.309
Yes.

01:20:37.420 --> 01:20:38.307
Of America?

01:20:38.420 --> 01:20:39.467
Yes.

01:20:39.620 --> 01:20:41.827
Wrote you a letter...

01:20:41.940 --> 01:20:43.226
personally?

01:20:43.340 --> 01:20:44.626
Yes.

01:20:44.740 --> 01:20:46.868
Personally, as in "Dear Major Warren"?

01:20:46.980 --> 01:20:49.187
No, personally, as in "Dear Marquis."

01:20:49.300 --> 01:20:50.461
"Dear Marquis"?

01:20:50.580 --> 01:20:53.704
Abraham Lincoln, the president
of the United States of America?

01:20:53.820 --> 01:20:54.946
Yes.

01:20:55.060 --> 01:20:56.949
May I see it?

01:20:57.060 --> 01:20:58.710
No, you may not.

01:20:59.780 --> 01:21:03.549
But the way John tells it, you weren't
just some random nigger soldier

01:21:03.660 --> 01:21:05.708
picked from a pile of letters.

01:21:05.820 --> 01:21:08.949
Way John tells it...

01:21:09.060 --> 01:21:10.983
y'all had a correspondence.

01:21:11.100 --> 01:21:12.340
Yes.

01:21:12.460 --> 01:21:14.508
The way John tells it...

01:21:14.620 --> 01:21:18.181
y'all was practically pen pals.

01:21:18.300 --> 01:21:20.621
Yes.

01:21:20.740 --> 01:21:23.664
And a pen pal's...

01:21:23.780 --> 01:21:26.181
practically a friend.

01:21:29.420 --> 01:21:31.741
(LAUGHING LOUDLY)

01:21:37.260 --> 01:21:39.467
John Ruth...

01:21:39.580 --> 01:21:41.503
you really think a nigger,

01:21:41.620 --> 01:21:44.863
drummed out of the cavalry with
a yellow stripe down his back,

01:21:45.020 --> 01:21:46.545
was practically friends

01:21:46.660 --> 01:21:49.106
with the president of
the United States of America?

01:21:49.220 --> 01:21:51.461
(CHRIS LAUGHING LOUDLY)

01:21:53.060 --> 01:21:55.711
John Ruth, I hate to be the one
to break it to you,

01:21:55.860 --> 01:21:58.591
but ain't nobody in Minnie's
Haberdashery ever corresponded

01:21:58.740 --> 01:22:00.788
with Abraham Lincoln.

01:22:00.900 --> 01:22:04.623
Least of all, that nigger there!

01:22:04.740 --> 01:22:06.549
(LAUGHING)

01:22:11.100 --> 01:22:12.306
(SLURPS)

01:22:14.060 --> 01:22:16.347
Was all that horseshit?

01:22:17.900 --> 01:22:20.221
(LAUGHS QUIETLY) Course it was.

01:22:20.340 --> 01:22:22.820
(LAUGHING LOUDLY)

01:22:22.940 --> 01:22:25.341
(DOMERGUE CACKLING)

01:22:26.540 --> 01:22:28.907
(BREATHLESS LAUGHING)

01:22:30.140 --> 01:22:32.791
DOMERGUE: Good one, Warren!

01:22:32.940 --> 01:22:34.704
Talk that sass, nigger!

01:22:34.860 --> 01:22:37.227
Talk that sass!

01:22:37.340 --> 01:22:38.865
(DOMERGUE SPITS)

01:22:38.980 --> 01:22:41.301
(MOANING, LAUGHING)

01:22:43.140 --> 01:22:44.505
(DOMERGUE SNORTS)

01:22:46.980 --> 01:22:50.541
Well, I guess it's true
what they say about you people.

01:22:53.500 --> 01:22:56.788
Can't trust a fuckin' word
comes out of your mouth.

01:22:56.900 --> 01:23:00.461
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)
What's the matter, John Ruth?

01:23:00.580 --> 01:23:02.264
I hurt your feelings?

01:23:02.380 --> 01:23:04.701
As a matter of fact...

01:23:04.820 --> 01:23:06.629
you did.

01:23:06.740 --> 01:23:09.630
- (WIND HOWLING)
- (SIGHS)

01:23:09.740 --> 01:23:11.504
I know...

01:23:11.620 --> 01:23:14.385
I'm the only black son of a
bitch you ever conversed with,

01:23:14.500 --> 01:23:16.468
so I'm gonna cut you some slack.

01:23:16.580 --> 01:23:19.345
But you got no idea what it's like

01:23:19.460 --> 01:23:22.304
being a black man facin' down America.

01:23:22.420 --> 01:23:24.787
Only time black folks is safe

01:23:24.900 --> 01:23:27.187
is when white folks is disarmed.

01:23:27.300 --> 01:23:31.305
And this letter had the desired effect

01:23:31.420 --> 01:23:34.344
of disarmin' white folks.

01:23:35.900 --> 01:23:38.665
Call it what you want. (CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

01:23:38.780 --> 01:23:41.784
I call it a dirty fuckin' trick.

01:23:46.380 --> 01:23:48.144
(SIGHS)

01:23:51.060 --> 01:23:53.540
You want to know why I lie

01:23:53.660 --> 01:23:56.106
about somethin' like that, white man?

01:24:00.340 --> 01:24:03.628
