♪ Now day and night the irons clang ♪

01:41:32.180 --> 01:41:35.901
♪ And like poor galley slaves ♪

01:41:36.020 --> 01:41:39.069
♪ We toil and toil and when we die ♪

01:41:39.180 --> 01:41:42.787
♪ Must fill dishonored graves ♪

01:41:42.900 --> 01:41:45.665
♪ By and by I'll break my chains ♪

01:41:45.780 --> 01:41:50.707
♪ And to the bush I'll go ♪

01:41:50.820 --> 01:41:55.781
♪ And you'll be dead behind me, John ♪

01:41:55.900 --> 01:41:59.586
♪ When I get to Mexico. ♪

01:42:05.020 --> 01:42:06.385
(SONG ENDS)

01:42:06.500 --> 01:42:08.980
Give me that guitar.

01:42:11.500 --> 01:42:12.786
Music time's over!

01:42:12.900 --> 01:42:14.106
DOMERGUE: Wha... Hey!

01:42:14.220 --> 01:42:15.631
Whoa! Whoa, whoa!

01:42:15.740 --> 01:42:16.980
Whoa!

01:42:17.100 --> 01:42:19.068
Turn around!

01:42:26.420 --> 01:42:27.910
John, no!

01:42:28.020 --> 01:42:29.545
- No, no, no, no, no!
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah!

01:42:29.660 --> 01:42:31.981
Shut up!

01:42:38.820 --> 01:42:40.788
(♪♪♪)

01:42:51.780 --> 01:42:53.544
(MATCH STRIKES)

01:43:11.100 --> 01:43:13.068
(♪♪♪)

01:43:31.140 --> 01:43:33.507
(♪♪♪)

01:43:40.940 --> 01:43:42.783
(BLOWS)

01:43:44.980 --> 01:43:48.541
(RETCHING)

01:43:54.220 --> 01:43:56.791
(GRUNTING)

01:44:07.900 --> 01:44:10.221
(O.B. GROANING)

01:44:15.340 --> 01:44:18.947
When you get to hell, John,

01:44:19.060 --> 01:44:21.028
tell 'em Daisy sent ya.

01:44:27.380 --> 01:44:29.223
(YELLS)

01:44:29.380 --> 01:44:31.109
(DOMERGUE GRUNTS)

01:44:34.380 --> 01:44:37.827
Mannix, the coffee!

01:44:43.180 --> 01:44:45.228
(JOHN GROANING)

01:44:57.700 --> 01:45:00.021
(GRUNTING AND GROANING)

01:45:05.980 --> 01:45:07.141
(LAUGHS)

01:45:07.260 --> 01:45:08.944
(GROANS)

01:45:13.900 --> 01:45:16.028
(CACKLING)

01:45:17.820 --> 01:45:20.187
(GROANING)

01:45:26.500 --> 01:45:27.786
(GUN CLICKS)

01:45:27.940 --> 01:45:28.987
(GROANS)

01:45:29.100 --> 01:45:31.148
(SIGHS)

01:45:31.260 --> 01:45:33.183
- (GUNSHOT)
- CHRIS: Oh, my God!

01:45:33.300 --> 01:45:35.826
Oh! Aah!

01:45:35.940 --> 01:45:36.987
(GUN CLICKS)

01:45:37.100 --> 01:45:38.465
WARREN: Give me that fucking gun.

01:45:38.580 --> 01:45:39.581
(PANTING)

01:45:39.740 --> 01:45:41.902
Don't test me, bitch.

01:45:45.180 --> 01:45:46.625
Everybody!

01:45:46.740 --> 01:45:50.303
Get your backsides up against
that back wall over yonder.

01:45:50.460 --> 01:45:52.940
Well, goddamn it!

01:45:53.060 --> 01:45:54.949
Get or don't get, Joe Gage.

01:45:55.060 --> 01:45:56.471
It's up to you.

01:45:56.580 --> 01:45:58.742
- I'm gettin'.
- Then get!

01:45:58.860 --> 01:46:00.828
(WIND WHISTLING)

01:46:11.100 --> 01:46:13.068
You, too, Senor Bob.

01:46:18.100 --> 01:46:21.668
Everybody turn around
and put your hands on that wall.

01:46:25.740 --> 01:46:27.822
Move them damn snowshoes!

01:46:41.540 --> 01:46:43.224
(SNORTS)

01:46:43.340 --> 01:46:45.308
(PANTING)

01:46:49.020 --> 01:46:50.863
Everybody keep your mouths shut.

01:46:51.020 --> 01:46:52.590
Do like I say.

01:46:52.700 --> 01:46:56.582
You open your mouth, you gonna get a bullet.

01:46:56.700 --> 01:46:59.425
Move a little sudden, a little strange,

01:46:59.540 --> 01:47:01.781
you gonna get a bullet.

01:47:01.900 --> 01:47:04.141
Not a warnin', not a question.

01:47:04.260 --> 01:47:05.989
A bullet.

01:47:06.100 --> 01:47:08.421
You got that?

01:47:08.580 --> 01:47:09.991
Let me hear you say, "I got it!"

01:47:10.100 --> 01:47:11.386
- I got it.
- I got it.

01:47:11.540 --> 01:47:12.621
I got it.

01:47:12.740 --> 01:47:14.424
We have it.

01:47:15.900 --> 01:47:17.902
Chris Mannix, come over here on this side.

01:47:19.540 --> 01:47:20.905
Come on.

01:47:26.180 --> 01:47:28.148
Take this gun out my holster.

01:47:39.100 --> 01:47:40.943
(WHISPERING): Point it at them.

01:47:42.340 --> 01:47:44.263
Now, like I said,

01:47:44.380 --> 01:47:47.145
anybody does anything,

01:47:47.260 --> 01:47:49.581
and I mean anything,

01:47:49.700 --> 01:47:51.384
you kill 'em.

01:47:52.660 --> 01:47:55.061
(GUN CLICKS)

01:47:55.180 --> 01:47:56.944
So...

01:47:57.060 --> 01:47:58.949
you finally decided I'm tellin' the truth

01:47:59.060 --> 01:48:01.108
about bein' the sheriff of Red Rock, huh?

01:48:02.780 --> 01:48:04.942
I don't know about all that.

01:48:05.060 --> 01:48:07.540
But I know you ain't the killer
poisoned that coffee,

01:48:07.660 --> 01:48:10.186
'cause you almost drunk it
your own damn self.

01:48:10.300 --> 01:48:11.870
One of them is.

01:48:17.180 --> 01:48:18.261
Aah!

01:48:18.380 --> 01:48:20.382
Ow!

01:48:20.500 --> 01:48:23.310
Give me the key. Give me the key!

01:48:35.260 --> 01:48:39.060
(YELLS) You motherfucking black bastard!

01:48:39.180 --> 01:48:43.861
You're gonna die on this mountain,
and I'm gonna fucking laugh when you do!

01:48:43.980 --> 01:48:45.550
(GASPS)

01:48:45.660 --> 01:48:47.310
WARREN: What'd I say 'bout talkin'?

01:48:47.420 --> 01:48:48.501
(MUTTERING): Bastard.

01:48:48.620 --> 01:48:50.987
Meant it, didn't I?

01:48:52.180 --> 01:48:56.027
And you need to understand
you just killed the only man here

01:48:56.140 --> 01:48:59.269
committed to gettin' you to Red Rock alive.

01:49:05.060 --> 01:49:07.108
Now, one of y'all...

01:49:07.220 --> 01:49:10.190
is workin' with her.

01:49:10.300 --> 01:49:12.348
Or two of y'all is workin' with her.

01:49:12.460 --> 01:49:15.111
Or all y'all is.

01:49:17.740 --> 01:49:21.105
But only one of you poisoned the coffee.

01:49:24.940 --> 01:49:27.625
Now, what charms this bitch got

01:49:27.740 --> 01:49:30.425
make a man brave a blizzard,

01:49:30.540 --> 01:49:32.383
kill in cold blood?

01:49:32.500 --> 01:49:34.104
(CHUCKLES)

01:49:34.220 --> 01:49:36.222
I'm sure I don't know.

01:49:40.100 --> 01:49:43.422
But John Ruth's tryin' to hang your woman.

01:49:43.540 --> 01:49:45.349
So you kill him.

01:49:45.460 --> 01:49:47.269
Okay.

01:49:47.380 --> 01:49:49.382
Maybe.

01:49:49.500 --> 01:49:52.663
But O.B. wasn't hangin' nobody.

01:49:52.780 --> 01:49:54.145
He damn sure wasn't.

01:49:54.260 --> 01:49:56.986
But he sure enough layin' over there
dead now, though, ain't he?

01:49:57.100 --> 01:49:59.182
He damn sure is, you sons of bitches.

01:49:59.300 --> 01:50:02.065
Just like any one of us
would've drunk that coffee.

01:50:02.180 --> 01:50:04.308
Like me, goddamn it.

01:50:04.420 --> 01:50:07.390
Now, those of y'all
with your hands on the wall

01:50:07.500 --> 01:50:10.549
don't practice in poison
need to think about that.

01:50:12.220 --> 01:50:16.625
Think about how it could've been you
rollin' around here on this floor.

01:50:16.740 --> 01:50:20.790
And how the man standin' next
to you would be responsible.

01:50:20.940 --> 01:50:23.386
And I know who I got my money on.

01:50:23.500 --> 01:50:25.867
Oh, that's right, Joe Gage.

01:50:25.980 --> 01:50:27.345
I'm lookin' at you.

01:50:29.340 --> 01:50:31.741
Not so fast, Chris.

01:50:31.860 --> 01:50:34.022
We'll get there.

01:50:34.140 --> 01:50:37.144
Let's slow it down.

01:50:37.260 --> 01:50:39.706
Let's slow it way down.

01:50:41.660 --> 01:50:43.185
(GUN CLICKS)

01:50:45.220 --> 01:50:46.984
Who made the coffee?

01:50:47.100 --> 01:50:48.704
He did.

01:50:50.740 --> 01:50:52.230
Yeah, he did, didn't he?

01:50:52.340 --> 01:50:55.389
Yeah, he did, didn't he?

01:50:55.500 --> 01:50:58.709
But it's the stew that's got me thinkin'.

01:51:00.140 --> 01:51:03.064
Now, how long you said Minnie been gone?

01:51:03.180 --> 01:51:04.750
A week?

01:51:05.900 --> 01:51:07.345
Si.

01:51:08.420 --> 01:51:10.070
See...

01:51:10.180 --> 01:51:13.150
my mama used to make stew,

01:51:13.260 --> 01:51:16.825
and it always tasted the same,
no matter the meat.

01:51:16.940 --> 01:51:18.863
And there was another fellow
on the plantation,

01:51:18.980 --> 01:51:20.505
Uncle Charly.

01:51:20.620 --> 01:51:22.145
He made stew, too.

01:51:22.260 --> 01:51:23.944
And like my mama,

01:51:24.060 --> 01:51:27.951
I ate his stew from the time I was a whipper

01:51:28.060 --> 01:51:30.461
till I was a full-grown man.

01:51:31.660 --> 01:51:33.583
No matter the meat,

01:51:33.700 --> 01:51:36.544
it always tasted like Uncle Charly's stew.

01:51:37.820 --> 01:51:41.463
Now, I ain't had Minnie's stew
in six months, so I ain't no expert.

01:51:41.580 --> 01:51:45.665
But that damn sure is...

01:51:45.780 --> 01:51:48.465
Minnie's stew.

01:51:48.580 --> 01:51:50.947
So if Minnie is on the north side

01:51:51.060 --> 01:51:53.540
visitin' her mama for a week,

01:51:53.700 --> 01:51:56.510
how'd she make the stew this mornin'?

01:51:56.660 --> 01:51:58.185
CHRIS: Hmm. (CHUCKLES)

01:51:58.300 --> 01:52:00.701
(BOB SIGHS)

01:52:00.820 --> 01:52:03.710
And this...

01:52:03.820 --> 01:52:07.620
this is Sweet Dave's chair.

01:52:07.740 --> 01:52:09.788
When I sat in it earlier,

01:52:09.900 --> 01:52:11.709
(CHUCKLING): I couldn't believe it.

01:52:11.820 --> 01:52:14.346
Nobody sits in Sweet Dave's chair.

01:52:14.460 --> 01:52:16.701
Uh, this may be Minnie's place,

01:52:16.820 --> 01:52:20.108
but this is damn sure

01:52:20.220 --> 01:52:22.302
Sweet Dave's chair.

01:52:24.620 --> 01:52:27.783
And if he went to the north side...

01:52:29.540 --> 01:52:31.781
I'm pretty goddamn sure

01:52:31.900 --> 01:52:34.585
this chair be goin' with him.

01:52:39.220 --> 01:52:41.063
What's in the chair?

01:52:41.180 --> 01:52:43.342
Just what I thought.

01:52:43.500 --> 01:52:46.470
Sweet Dave's goddamn blood.

01:52:46.580 --> 01:52:48.230
Hoo!

01:52:48.380 --> 01:52:50.064
Hoo-hoo-hoo!

01:52:52.180 --> 01:52:56.504
So, are you actually accusing me of murder?

01:52:56.620 --> 01:52:58.349
(WARREN CHUCKLES)

01:52:59.700 --> 01:53:02.670
Way I see it, Senor Bob,

01:53:02.780 --> 01:53:05.943
is whoever is workin' with her

01:53:06.060 --> 01:53:08.904
ain't who they say they is.

01:53:09.020 --> 01:53:10.863
And if it's you,

01:53:10.980 --> 01:53:13.108
that means Minnie and her man

01:53:13.220 --> 01:53:15.063
ain't at her mama's.

01:53:15.180 --> 01:53:18.662
They layin' out back there dead somewhere.

01:53:18.780 --> 01:53:20.828
Or if it's you, little British man,

01:53:20.940 --> 01:53:24.149
the real Oswaldo Mobray layin'
in a ditch somewhere

01:53:24.260 --> 01:53:26.786
and you just a English fella
passin' off his papers.

01:53:26.900 --> 01:53:29.665
CHRIS: Or we go by my theory,

01:53:29.780 --> 01:53:32.704
which is the ugliest guy did it.

01:53:32.820 --> 01:53:35.391
Which makes it you, Joe Gage.

01:53:35.500 --> 01:53:39.789
So I take it you deduced
the coffee was poisoned

01:53:39.900 --> 01:53:41.868
while you were murdering the old man?

01:53:43.060 --> 01:53:44.710
Yes.

01:53:44.820 --> 01:53:47.346
Well, mi negro amigo,

01:53:47.460 --> 01:53:49.622
during that whole incident,

01:53:49.740 --> 01:53:52.346
I was sitting on that side of the room

01:53:52.460 --> 01:53:54.667
playing "Silent Night" on the piano.

01:53:54.820 --> 01:53:57.824
Oh, I ain't say you poisoned the coffee.

01:53:57.940 --> 01:54:00.910
I said you didn't make the stew.

01:54:02.420 --> 01:54:05.902
My theory is...

01:54:06.020 --> 01:54:09.024
you workin' with the man

01:54:09.140 --> 01:54:13.341
who poisoned the coffee,
and both of y'all murdered Minnie,

01:54:13.460 --> 01:54:16.384
Sweet Dave and whoever else
picked this bad-luck day

01:54:16.500 --> 01:54:19.344
to visit Minnie's Haberdashery this mornin'.

01:54:19.460 --> 01:54:23.226
And at some point, y'all intended

01:54:23.340 --> 01:54:25.820
to bushwhack John Ruth

01:54:25.940 --> 01:54:28.705
and free Daisy.

01:54:28.820 --> 01:54:31.266
But you didn't count on the blizzard,

01:54:31.380 --> 01:54:34.429
and you didn't count on the two of us.

01:54:34.540 --> 01:54:35.701
CHRIS: Hmm.

01:54:39.100 --> 01:54:41.068
That's far as I got. How am I doing?

01:54:41.180 --> 01:54:43.148
(CHUCKLES)

01:54:44.980 --> 01:54:47.426
You're a real imaginative nigger,

01:54:47.580 --> 01:54:49.787
- ain't you?
- (LAUGHS)

01:54:49.900 --> 01:54:52.744
So, do you intend to murder me

01:54:52.860 --> 01:54:55.181
based on a far-fetched nigger theory,

01:54:55.340 --> 01:54:57.707
or can you prove it, cabron?

01:54:57.820 --> 01:54:59.106
(LAUGHS)

01:54:59.260 --> 01:55:04.391
It ain't so far-fetched, Senor Bob.

01:55:04.500 --> 01:55:07.265
And it's a little bit more than a theory.

01:55:11.620 --> 01:55:14.191
How long you say you been workin' for Minnie?

01:55:14.300 --> 01:55:16.064
Four months.

01:55:16.180 --> 01:55:17.909
Mmm.

01:55:18.020 --> 01:55:20.705
See, if you'd have been here
two and a half years ago,

01:55:20.820 --> 01:55:24.666
you'd know 'bout that sign
used to hang up over the bar.

01:55:24.780 --> 01:55:27.226
Minnie mention that to you?

01:55:28.540 --> 01:55:30.383
No.

01:55:30.540 --> 01:55:33.305
You want to know what
that sign said, Senor Bob?

01:55:35.460 --> 01:55:39.749
"No dogs or Mexicans allowed."

01:55:39.860 --> 01:55:43.103
(CHRIS LAUGHS)

01:55:43.260 --> 01:55:46.822
Now, Minnie hung that sign up
the day she opened this haberdashery.

01:55:46.940 --> 01:55:49.910
And it hung over that bar every day

01:55:50.060 --> 01:55:53.030
till she took it down
a little over two years ago.

01:55:54.620 --> 01:55:56.384
You know why she took it down?

01:55:58.260 --> 01:56:00.786
She started lettin' in dogs.

01:56:00.900 --> 01:56:02.868
(SIGHS)

01:56:04.460 --> 01:56:08.431
Now, Minnie liked just about everybody,

01:56:08.580 --> 01:56:10.708
but she sure don't

01:56:10.820 --> 01:56:12.663
like Mexicans.

01:56:12.780 --> 01:56:14.703
So when you tell me

01:56:14.820 --> 01:56:18.381
Minnie went to the north side
to visit her mama,

01:56:18.500 --> 01:56:21.071
well, I find that highly unlikely.

01:56:21.180 --> 01:56:24.468
But okay, maybe.

01:56:24.580 --> 01:56:27.186
But when you tell me

01:56:27.300 --> 01:56:30.941
Minnie Mink took the haberdashery,

01:56:31.100 --> 01:56:35.025
the most precious thing to her
in the whole world,

01:56:35.140 --> 01:56:39.111
and left it in the hands
of a goddamn Mexican?

01:56:40.580 --> 01:56:42.230
Well, that's what I meant in the barn

01:56:42.340 --> 01:56:45.071
when I said that sure
don't sound like Minnie.

01:56:47.140 --> 01:56:50.144
Now I am calling you a liar,

01:56:50.260 --> 01:56:52.228
Senor Bob.

01:56:53.500 --> 01:56:55.502
And if you lyin',

01:56:55.620 --> 01:56:57.110
which you are...

01:56:58.740 --> 01:56:59.707
then you killed Minnie.

01:56:59.820 --> 01:57:01.743
- And Sweet Dave.
- (GROANING)

01:57:12.460 --> 01:57:13.621
(CLICKING)

01:57:20.180 --> 01:57:22.581
Four measly bullets,

01:57:22.700 --> 01:57:25.829
and there goes Senor Bob.

01:57:27.460 --> 01:57:30.782
But that still don't get us no closer

01:57:30.900 --> 01:57:34.268
to which one of y'all
poisoned the coffee, though.

01:57:34.380 --> 01:57:35.427
Do it, Chris?

01:57:35.580 --> 01:57:37.548
CHRIS: No, it sure don't.

01:57:39.780 --> 01:57:42.101
(CHUCKLES)

01:57:43.580 --> 01:57:45.901
Now, one of y'all poisoned this coffee

01:57:46.020 --> 01:57:47.431
to free Daisy.

01:57:47.540 --> 01:57:49.224
If I don't hear a confession

01:57:49.340 --> 01:57:52.469
from one of you motherfuckers
quick, fast and in a hurry,

01:57:52.580 --> 01:57:55.151
I'm gonna pour this whole pot of coffee

01:57:55.260 --> 01:57:57.866
down that bitch's goddamn throat.

01:57:59.180 --> 01:58:02.343
Okay. Time's up.

01:58:02.460 --> 01:58:03.746
JOE: Stop!

01:58:03.900 --> 01:58:05.789
All right, I did it.

01:58:05.900 --> 01:58:07.823
It was me. I poisoned the coffee.

01:58:08.940 --> 01:58:11.910
I fuckin' knew it!

01:58:12.020 --> 01:58:13.465
Oh!

01:58:13.620 --> 01:58:15.987
You gonna die now, you murderin' bastard!

01:58:16.100 --> 01:58:19.149
Major Warren, please let me send this ugly

01:58:19.260 --> 01:58:21.149
son of a bitch to hell.

01:58:21.260 --> 01:58:23.069
You killed O.B.

01:58:23.180 --> 01:58:24.784
He was worth ten of you.

01:58:24.900 --> 01:58:26.584
Warren, can I kill him?

01:58:26.700 --> 01:58:27.906
Say adios to your huevos.

01:58:28.020 --> 01:58:29.067
(GUN CLICKS, FIRES)

01:58:29.220 --> 01:58:32.827
(SCREAMING)

01:58:35.420 --> 01:58:38.185
(DISTORTED): Major Warren!

01:58:41.420 --> 01:58:43.263
(DISTORTED GROANING)

01:58:48.100 --> 01:58:49.590
(BULLET RICOCHETING)

01:58:49.740 --> 01:58:51.981
(GROANING)

01:58:52.100 --> 01:58:55.183
(WARREN SCREAMING)

01:58:55.300 --> 01:58:58.543
(DISTORTED): I ain't got no gun,

01:58:58.660 --> 01:59:01.106
Sheriff.

01:59:01.220 --> 01:59:03.427
(SCREAMING)

01:59:15.540 --> 01:59:18.589
(SCREAMING)

01:59:31.500 --> 01:59:33.502
(♪♪♪)

01:59:35.700 --> 01:59:37.065
- WOMAN: Roy!
- (WHISTLING)

01:59:37.180 --> 01:59:38.784
Good boy.

01:59:40.260 --> 01:59:42.547
(WHISTLES)

01:59:42.660 --> 01:59:44.185
(WHISTLES) Get up!

01:59:44.300 --> 01:59:45.426
Get up there!

01:59:45.540 --> 01:59:46.666
Get up!

01:59:46.780 --> 01:59:49.431
Packer, Roy, get up!

01:59:49.540 --> 01:59:51.144
Get up!

01:59:51.300 --> 01:59:52.586
- Get up there! Get up!
- (WHISTLES)

01:59:52.700 --> 01:59:53.826
Get up!

01:59:53.940 --> 01:59:55.180
Get up there! Get up!

01:59:55.300 --> 01:59:56.870
Get up!

01:59:56.980 --> 01:59:58.186
MAN: Go!

02:00:00.540 --> 02:00:03.987
Go! Go! Go!

02:00:04.100 --> 02:00:06.421
Go! Go!

02:00:08.540 --> 02:00:09.905
Go!

02:00:10.020 --> 02:00:12.341
(WHOOPING)

02:00:14.980 --> 02:00:17.460
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

02:00:17.620 --> 02:00:19.702
(♪♪♪)

02:00:33.380 --> 02:00:35.348
(♪♪♪)

02:00:52.060 --> 02:00:54.381
(♪♪♪)

02:01:10.940 --> 02:01:12.510
Get up. Get up.

02:01:12.620 --> 02:01:14.748
- (WHISTLES) Hyah! Get up! Get up!
- Get up!

02:01:14.860 --> 02:01:15.907
Get up!

02:01:16.020 --> 02:01:17.624
(WHISTLES) Get up!

02:01:26.300 --> 02:01:27.540
MAN: Get up!

02:01:27.660 --> 02:01:30.061
WOMAN: Get up!

02:01:33.700 --> 02:01:35.304
Get up! Get up!

02:01:35.420 --> 02:01:37.582
(SHOUTING)

02:01:51.580 --> 02:01:52.866
- Whoa!
- Easy.

02:01:52.980 --> 02:01:54.106
- Whoa.
- Whoa!

02:01:54.260 --> 02:01:56.149
Whoa. Hey, Charly, my boy.

02:01:56.300 --> 02:01:57.347
How the hell are you?

02:01:57.460 --> 02:01:58.871
Hiya, Ed. Hiya, Judy.

02:01:58.980 --> 02:02:00.391
Yeah!

02:02:00.500 --> 02:02:01.501
(CHUCKLES)

02:02:01.620 --> 02:02:02.587
Ah.

02:02:02.700 --> 02:02:03.861
How many you got?

02:02:03.980 --> 02:02:05.027
Full house today, friend.

02:02:05.140 --> 02:02:06.630
Got one in there waitin'.

02:02:06.740 --> 02:02:08.105
Well, he's gonna have to keep on waitin'.

02:02:08.220 --> 02:02:09.221
We ain't got no room.

02:02:09.340 --> 02:02:10.671
Well, you need to tell Minnie.

02:02:10.780 --> 02:02:13.705
'Cause he been here two days,
and Minnie wants him out of here.

02:02:13.860 --> 02:02:15.703
Well, I can't give him a seat I don't have.

02:02:15.860 --> 02:02:18.340
Listen, why don't you take
the passengers inside

02:02:18.460 --> 02:02:21.305
and introduce 'em to Minnie,
warm yourself up and drink some coffee.

02:02:21.420 --> 02:02:22.501
Yeah.

02:02:27.780 --> 02:02:29.509
Here we are, everybody.

02:02:29.620 --> 02:02:30.951
Minnie's Haberdashery.

02:02:31.060 --> 02:02:33.586
Step outside, you and your friends
can stretch your legs.

02:02:33.700 --> 02:02:37.347
When you're ready, step on inside, get
warm by the fire, get some coffee in you.

02:02:37.460 --> 02:02:39.269
I'll introduce you to Minnie.

02:02:42.460 --> 02:02:45.145
Hiya, Minnie!

02:02:45.260 --> 02:02:47.228
(♪♪♪)

02:03:02.860 --> 02:03:04.624
JUDY: Now, Minnie, I'm not tryin' to tell you

02:03:04.740 --> 02:03:06.663
how to run your business,
but I would think coffee

02:03:06.780 --> 02:03:09.021
- would be the first thing you'd make.
- Hmm.

02:03:09.140 --> 02:03:10.505
Come on in, everybody. Don't be shy.

02:03:10.620 --> 02:03:12.065
Hats!

02:03:12.180 --> 02:03:14.547
Everybody, this is Minnie,
and this is her place.

02:03:14.660 --> 02:03:17.869
Behind me, pluckin' that chicken, is Gemma.

02:03:17.980 --> 02:03:19.027
Ah.

02:03:19.140 --> 02:03:21.507
Lovely smile, that Gemma.

02:03:21.620 --> 02:03:23.384
Now, the fella in the uniform I don't know,

02:03:23.500 --> 02:03:25.502
but the one he's playing chess
with is Sweet Dave.

02:03:25.620 --> 02:03:26.781
Hiya, Dave.

02:03:26.900 --> 02:03:28.868
- Hey, Judy.
- (JUDY CHUCKLES)

02:03:29.020 --> 02:03:32.105
And, Minnie, these are the passengers.

02:03:32.220 --> 02:03:34.109
Well, that's not good enough.

02:03:34.220 --> 02:03:36.063
Go on, take away them rags,

02:03:36.180 --> 02:03:38.421
let's see some faces, let's hear some names.

02:03:38.540 --> 02:03:41.146
Oswaldo Mobray, madam.

02:03:41.260 --> 02:03:42.546
Joe Gage.

02:03:42.700 --> 02:03:44.782
Bob.

02:03:44.900 --> 02:03:46.504
And I'm Jody.

02:03:46.660 --> 02:03:49.266
It's a pleasant surprise
to find such a warm sanctuary

02:03:49.380 --> 02:03:51.587
in the middle of such a cold hell.

02:03:51.700 --> 02:03:53.225
Well, make yourself comfortable.

02:03:53.340 --> 02:03:54.626
Get warm by the fire.

02:03:54.740 --> 02:03:56.788
Uh, we're just gonna go warm ourselves

02:03:56.900 --> 02:03:58.550
by the stove, if that's all right.

02:03:58.660 --> 02:04:00.424
Oh, stove, fireplace, whatever.

02:04:00.540 --> 02:04:01.541
Just get warm.

02:04:01.660 --> 02:04:04.784
Oh, and Judy said somethin'
about the best coffee in the world.

02:04:04.900 --> 02:04:06.902
Ah, yes. I do believe Judy did say something

02:04:07.020 --> 02:04:09.341
about the best coffee in the world.

02:04:09.460 --> 02:04:12.470
Well, I don't know about all that,
but I tell you what it is.

02:04:12.580 --> 02:04:14.105
It's hot, it's strong, and it's good.

02:04:14.220 --> 02:04:17.190
And in this here snow,
it sure enough warms your ass up.

02:04:17.300 --> 02:04:19.621
You don't need to sell it,
Minnie, you need to make it.

02:04:19.780 --> 02:04:21.305
And you need to get your ass out there

02:04:21.420 --> 02:04:23.502
and help Charly with them bags
and get Ed in here.

02:04:23.620 --> 02:04:25.349
Yes, ma'am.

02:04:25.460 --> 02:04:27.462
- But fix that coffee.
- I'll fix you!

02:04:27.620 --> 02:04:29.827
(DOOR CREAKS OPEN AND SHUT)

02:04:29.940 --> 02:04:31.590
I don't know, some old man.

02:04:31.700 --> 02:04:33.828
Well, I don't know what
I'm supposed to do about it.

02:04:33.940 --> 02:04:35.863
I'm just telling you what she said.

02:04:35.980 --> 02:04:37.789
Anyway, she sent me out here to help Charly.

02:04:37.900 --> 02:04:40.380
- She wants to talk to you.
- (BIRD SQUAWKING)

02:04:40.500 --> 02:04:42.150
Charly, you got a hold of these fellas?

02:04:42.300 --> 02:04:43.825
Got 'em, Ed.

02:05:00.300 --> 02:05:03.463
Miss Minnie, would you roll me a cigarette?

02:05:03.580 --> 02:05:04.991
Sure, honey.

02:05:05.100 --> 02:05:06.465
I smoke Red Apple tobacco.

02:05:06.580 --> 02:05:07.502
That all right?

02:05:07.660 --> 02:05:09.628
That's my favorite.

02:05:12.620 --> 02:05:15.385
Don't mind me, gentlemen.

02:05:15.540 --> 02:05:17.986
I'm just watching.

02:05:18.100 --> 02:05:20.785
You play?

02:05:20.900 --> 02:05:25.030
You know, I must have had at least 12 people

02:05:25.140 --> 02:05:27.507
teach me that goddamn game.

02:05:27.620 --> 02:05:30.988
Just never could keep the moves in my head.

02:05:32.420 --> 02:05:35.341
But if I'm not disturbing, I'd like to watch.

02:05:35.460 --> 02:05:38.749
Hell no. I like whippin' this old man's
ass in front of a audience.

02:05:38.900 --> 02:05:41.267
- (CHUCKLES)
- You ain't whippin' shit!

02:05:42.980 --> 02:05:45.506
Merci beaucoup, Mademoiselle Minnie.

02:05:45.620 --> 02:05:47.065
Oh, that's real nice.

02:05:47.180 --> 02:05:48.591
What is that?

02:05:48.740 --> 02:05:49.901
That's French.

02:05:50.020 --> 02:05:51.704
You speak French?

02:05:51.820 --> 02:05:53.185
Oui.

02:05:53.300 --> 02:05:55.541
"Oui"? What does that mean?

02:05:55.660 --> 02:05:57.389
It means "yes."

02:05:57.540 --> 02:05:59.781
Oui, yes.

02:05:59.900 --> 02:06:03.382
Hey, hey, Dave, ask me if my ass is fat.

02:06:03.500 --> 02:06:04.547
What?

02:06:04.660 --> 02:06:06.264
Ask me if my ass is fat.

02:06:06.380 --> 02:06:07.666
It is.

02:06:07.780 --> 02:06:09.430
I said ask me.

02:06:09.540 --> 02:06:10.746
Why?

02:06:10.860 --> 02:06:12.624
Just do it!

02:06:12.740 --> 02:06:14.583
Is your ass fat?

02:06:14.700 --> 02:06:16.145
Oui. (CHUCKLES)

02:06:16.260 --> 02:06:18.388
Look at that, y'all, I can speak French.

02:06:18.500 --> 02:06:20.662
(MINNIE CHUCKLING)

02:06:20.780 --> 02:06:23.624
(♪♪♪)

02:06:25.300 --> 02:06:26.426
(SIGHS)

02:06:26.540 --> 02:06:28.508
(CLEARS THROAT)

02:06:46.700 --> 02:06:48.668
(MINNIE CHUCKLES)

02:06:54.100 --> 02:06:56.102
(OSWALDO CLEARS THROAT)

02:06:56.220 --> 02:06:59.631
Are you the, uh,
jelly bean salesman around here?

02:06:59.740 --> 02:07:01.185
(GEMMA GIGGLES)

02:07:01.300 --> 02:07:03.587
How many peppermint sticks
I get for a nickel?

02:07:03.700 --> 02:07:05.702
Five.

02:07:05.860 --> 02:07:07.828
All right.

02:07:10.220 --> 02:07:12.427
- Here you go.
- Thank you, sugar.

02:07:12.540 --> 02:07:14.508
GEMMA (LAUGHING): Okay.

02:07:21.780 --> 02:07:24.909
Uh, allow me to assist you, madam.

02:07:25.020 --> 02:07:26.988
(♪♪♪)

02:07:39.380 --> 02:07:41.701
(DOOR OPENS)

02:07:45.260 --> 02:07:46.910
I'm bringing in your bags

02:07:47.020 --> 02:07:49.387
in case anybody wants to change
your clothes before Red Rock.

02:07:49.500 --> 02:07:51.025
Oh.

02:07:59.500 --> 02:08:02.310
Peppermint stick?

02:08:02.460 --> 02:08:05.384
(JUDY CHUCKLES)

02:08:06.620 --> 02:08:08.668
Thanks.

02:08:08.780 --> 02:08:10.066
(CHUCKLES)

02:08:11.780 --> 02:08:14.465
So why do they call you
"Six-Horse Judy" anyway?

02:08:16.180 --> 02:08:20.386
'Cause I'm the only Judy you've ever
seen that can drive a six-horse team.

02:08:20.500 --> 02:08:21.706
Oh, yeah.

02:08:21.820 --> 02:08:23.106
(BOTH LAUGHING)

02:08:23.220 --> 02:08:25.507
Kind of a stupid question.

02:08:25.620 --> 02:08:27.384
(BOTH LAUGHING)

02:08:27.500 --> 02:08:29.184
Do you mind holding this for me?

02:08:29.300 --> 02:08:31.029
Ah...

02:08:31.140 --> 02:08:33.871
rock steady, madam.

02:08:33.980 --> 02:08:36.631
Rock steady.

02:08:36.740 --> 02:08:40.825
(SNIFFS) You got a very sweet little accent.

02:08:40.940 --> 02:08:42.863
Where's that from, England?

02:08:42.980 --> 02:08:44.550
I take exception to that.

02:08:44.660 --> 02:08:46.105
(CHUCKLES)

02:08:46.220 --> 02:08:48.700
- JUDY: New Zealand.
- Careful, madam. Precarious.

02:08:48.820 --> 02:08:50.390
JOE: Is that anywhere near, uh, Old Zealand?

02:08:50.500 --> 02:08:52.901
(JUDY LAUGHS)

02:08:53.020 --> 02:08:54.988
(♪♪♪)

02:09:07.860 --> 02:09:09.828
(CHUCKLES)

02:09:10.980 --> 02:09:12.311
MINNIE: Mmm.

02:09:13.340 --> 02:09:14.751
JOE: Auckland?

02:09:14.860 --> 02:09:16.669
What the fuck's an Auckland?

02:09:16.780 --> 02:09:18.350
JUDY: It's where I'm from.

02:09:18.460 --> 02:09:20.030
It's our biggest city.

02:09:20.140 --> 02:09:21.630
- Coffee!
- Mm-hmm.

02:09:22.860 --> 02:09:24.225
Coffee's ready.

02:09:24.340 --> 02:09:26.149
Well, it's about damn time!

02:09:26.260 --> 02:09:28.069
(CHUCKLES)

02:09:28.180 --> 02:09:30.023
Best coffee on the mountain.

02:09:30.140 --> 02:09:32.347
MINNIE: Oh, I don't know about all that.

02:09:32.460 --> 02:09:35.748
Stagecoach drivers like it,
passengers not so much.

02:09:35.860 --> 02:09:38.181
Most find it a mite too strong.

02:09:38.300 --> 02:09:40.189
Can't be too strong on this mountain.

02:09:40.300 --> 02:09:41.461
- (MINNIE CHUCKLES)
- Thank you.

02:09:46.740 --> 02:09:48.185
MINNIE: Well?

02:09:48.300 --> 02:09:49.870
What do you think?

02:09:59.060 --> 02:10:00.471
(WIND WHISTLING)

02:10:00.620 --> 02:10:02.941
(GRUNTING)

02:10:06.940 --> 02:10:09.546
- (GRUNTS)
- (GROANING)

02:10:12.620 --> 02:10:13.701
Shit, fuck!

02:10:13.820 --> 02:10:16.061
(GASPING)

02:10:16.180 --> 02:10:17.705
Shit!

02:10:17.820 --> 02:10:20.391
(PANTING)

02:10:20.500 --> 02:10:22.867
(GROANS, GRUNTS)

02:10:22.980 --> 02:10:25.301
(PANTING, GASPING)

02:10:39.580 --> 02:10:40.820
BOB: Yep.

02:10:51.220 --> 02:10:53.348
- JODY: Mmm, si.
- BOB: He adds something.

02:10:53.460 --> 02:10:54.905
Not much, but something.

02:10:55.020 --> 02:10:56.829
(JODY SIGHS)

02:10:56.940 --> 02:10:58.385
What you think, Pete?

02:10:58.500 --> 02:11:00.468
(GUNSHOT)

02:11:02.700 --> 02:11:07.150
Well, I must admit, he does make
the setup more convincing.

02:11:07.260 --> 02:11:08.341
(JUDY WHIMPERING)

02:11:08.460 --> 02:11:09.586
JODY: Hmm.

02:11:09.700 --> 02:11:10.940
Okay.

02:11:11.060 --> 02:11:12.630
I'll talk to the old man.

02:11:12.740 --> 02:11:15.949
You three collect the bodies
and chuck 'em in that well out there.

02:11:17.460 --> 02:11:19.269
And then start unhitchin' the horses

02:11:19.380 --> 02:11:21.189
and gettin' 'em in the barn
and gettin' 'em fed.

02:11:21.300 --> 02:11:25.064
PETE: Well, hang on. I mean, puttin'
the horses away, that's easy enough,

02:11:25.180 --> 02:11:28.187
but draggin' these fat bastards up and down
the mountain, that's fuckin' impossible.

02:11:28.300 --> 02:11:29.950
- JODY: Okay.
- (JOE SPITS)

02:11:30.060 --> 02:11:32.427
JODY: Well, this is a store,
so there's gotta be

02:11:32.540 --> 02:11:34.065
a wheelbarrow around here somewhere.

02:11:34.180 --> 02:11:35.944
Start with the horses,

02:11:36.060 --> 02:11:39.951
and as soon as I get through
with this old hickory tree,

02:11:40.060 --> 02:11:42.267
I'll come out and help you, okay?

02:11:49.060 --> 02:11:51.461
BOB: Hey, Pete, grab my coat, will ya?

02:11:59.860 --> 02:12:01.828
(♪♪♪)

02:12:08.820 --> 02:12:10.743
♪ Now ♪

02:12:10.860 --> 02:12:12.703
♪ You're all ♪

02:12:12.820 --> 02:12:15.664
♪ Alone ♪

02:12:18.180 --> 02:12:19.989
♪ Feelin' ♪

02:12:20.100 --> 02:12:23.991
♪ That nobody wants you ♪

02:12:27.140 --> 02:12:29.586
♪ And you're looking ♪

02:12:29.700 --> 02:12:32.226
♪ For someone ♪

02:12:32.340 --> 02:12:36.948
♪ To hold your hand ♪

02:12:37.060 --> 02:12:39.825
- ♪ Someone ♪
- (CHUCKLING)

02:12:39.940 --> 02:12:44.628
♪ Who understands ♪

02:12:47.900 --> 02:12:49.504
♪ Now ♪

02:12:49.660 --> 02:12:53.460
♪ You're by yourself ♪

02:12:53.580 --> 02:12:55.582
(CLEARS THROAT)

02:12:55.700 --> 02:12:59.261
♪ And you're feelin' ♪

02:12:59.420 --> 02:13:02.264
♪ The world close ♪

02:13:02.380 --> 02:13:04.906
♪ In on you ♪

02:13:06.220 --> 02:13:08.461
♪ And you're askin'... ♪

02:13:08.580 --> 02:13:10.582
Look.

02:13:10.700 --> 02:13:12.384
I just started workin' here.

02:13:12.500 --> 02:13:14.468
Whatever Minnie did to make y'all mad...

02:13:15.740 --> 02:13:17.583
I had nothin' to do with it.

02:13:17.700 --> 02:13:19.270
♪ Someone... ♪

02:13:19.380 --> 02:13:21.382
- (GUNSHOT)
- (SONG ABRUPTLY ENDS)

02:13:21.500 --> 02:13:23.741
(WIND WHISTLING)

02:13:26.500 --> 02:13:28.468
JODY: Hmm.

02:13:29.740 --> 02:13:32.391
Well, old man.

02:13:34.100 --> 02:13:35.784
If you...

02:13:35.900 --> 02:13:37.504
was a cat,

02:13:37.620 --> 02:13:40.430
what just happened here

02:13:40.540 --> 02:13:42.781
would count as one of your nine lives.

02:13:45.500 --> 02:13:48.071
Do you realize how close you came

02:13:48.220 --> 02:13:50.109
to being tossed on a pile of niggers?

02:13:50.220 --> 02:13:51.745
- (CHUCKLES) Yes.
- Yeah.

02:13:51.860 --> 02:13:55.669
And when it comes to that pile
of niggers that we buildin' out back,

02:13:55.780 --> 02:13:57.669
won't take nothin' to make you general of it.

02:13:57.780 --> 02:13:59.942
You believe that?

02:14:00.060 --> 02:14:02.301
I expect no less.

02:14:02.420 --> 02:14:05.663
Not so fast, old man.

02:14:05.820 --> 02:14:07.822
You might have a way out of this yet.

02:14:11.020 --> 02:14:14.229
Later today,

02:14:14.340 --> 02:14:16.388
dirty...

02:14:16.540 --> 02:14:19.111
son of a gun

02:14:19.220 --> 02:14:21.427
is gonna come in here...

02:14:25.060 --> 02:14:27.950
and he's gonna have my sister with him.

02:14:28.060 --> 02:14:31.621
And he is gonna have her in chains.

02:14:34.660 --> 02:14:37.789
He's taking her to Red Rock to be hung.

02:14:47.940 --> 02:14:50.181
Do you know why?

02:14:50.300 --> 02:14:52.667
No.

02:14:55.700 --> 02:14:57.828
$10,000.

02:14:59.900 --> 02:15:03.063
That's why.

02:15:03.180 --> 02:15:05.103
Now, when he gets here,

02:15:05.220 --> 02:15:09.589
I'm gonna kill that fella
and turn my sister loose.

02:15:09.700 --> 02:15:13.591
Now, do you have any reason
why you would want to interfere

02:15:13.700 --> 02:15:16.670
with me saving my sister
from a hangman's rope?

02:15:16.780 --> 02:15:17.827
No.

02:15:17.940 --> 02:15:19.101
You don't?

02:15:19.220 --> 02:15:20.381
No, I don't.

02:15:20.500 --> 02:15:21.990
You sure you don't?

02:15:22.100 --> 02:15:25.183
I mean, we did just kill
Minnie and Sweet Dave.

02:15:26.300 --> 02:15:29.100
Now, you and Sweet Dave looked
mighty chummy over here.

02:15:29.220 --> 02:15:30.381
I just met these people!

02:15:30.500 --> 02:15:32.104
I don't give a damn about them!

02:15:32.220 --> 02:15:34.461
Or you. Or your sister.

02:15:34.620 --> 02:15:37.863
Or any other son of a bitch
in Wyoming, for that matter.

02:15:37.980 --> 02:15:41.382
That is a good answer,

02:15:41.540 --> 02:15:43.986
old man.

02:15:44.100 --> 02:15:46.262
Now, when they get here,

02:15:46.420 --> 02:15:49.424
you just sit your ass in this chair,

02:15:49.540 --> 02:15:51.702
and you don't do nothin'.

02:15:51.820 --> 02:15:53.026
You don't say nothin'.

02:15:53.180 --> 02:15:54.261
"Hello."

02:15:54.380 --> 02:15:55.302
"Thank you."

02:15:55.420 --> 02:15:56.421
"Good night."

02:15:56.540 --> 02:15:57.746
That's about it.

